name: Gregory Ellis
title: 🚀 Let's blast off
about:
My interest in consumer finance kicked off just after finishing my International Business and Economics degrees. Like many 20-somethings, I was terrible with money — “king for a day, fool for a fortnight.” Turns out I wasn’t the only one.

So in 2005, Sean Teahan and I co-founded Nimble — funded by the modest success of A-Team Health Recruitment and mowing a lot of lawns. We built a household brand that made small loans feel refreshingly simple. At the time, we had no idea we were pioneering fintech in Australia. Nimble grew to 150 staff and over $50 million in revenue.

Then in 2016, like many before me, I joined the not-so-exclusive club of founders ousted by their own boards. Cue a two-year sabbatical by the lake in Gandria, Switzerland, where I met my brilliant Spanish wife Miriam and helped launch Little Phil — a microphilanthropy app that gave donors their daily doce of 'Phil-good' moments.

In 2019, I jumped into another David vs Goliath project — my favourite kind — with some friends. We built Beeline, a US mortgage lender with beautiful UX, clever AI, and a mission to kill the soul-crushing home loan journey. We helped everyone from gig workers to property investors get home loans faster. Highlights: being listed on the NASDAQ and launching the world’s first AI mortgage sales assistant.

Now I’m advising the brilliant team at MagicBlocks — an AI startup doing some impressive work. These aren’t your usual rage-inducing, scripted ‘crapbots’. MagicBlocks’ agents are charismatic digital naturals — engaging 15x more visitors, listening, solving problems, and converting like nothing else — all while freeing up human teams.

When I’m not tweaking UX or poking holes in conversion funnels, I’m probably surfing, biking, doing yoga, tinkering with my putting stroke, or hanging with Miriam and our two little ones, Lola and Rapha.
experience_3_title: Co Founder Strategy Marketing and Product

name: Snehal Antani
title: CEO @ Horizon3.ai
about:
Bio:

Snehal Antani is CEO & co-founder of Horizon3.ai, a cyber security company that pioneered the use of AI to autonomously conduct penetration testing. 

Prior to Horizon3, Snehal served as the first Chief Technology Officer for Joint Special Operations Command (JSOC). As a member of the Commander’s executive team, he led data analytics, cloud/edge computing, and cybersecurity initiatives

Prior to serving within US Special Operations, Snehal was CTO & SVP at Splunk, held multiple CIO roles at GE Capital, and started his career as a Software Engineer at IBM. 

Snehal earned a Masters in Computer Science from Rensselaer Polytechnic University (RPI), a BS in Computer Science from Purdue University where he was their 2023 Distinguished Alumni, and holds 18 patents. 

What motivates me:

1. Purpose. I want to solve problems that matter
2. Impact. I'm not here to be incremental
3. Culture. Be a "learn it all", not a "know it all"

My leadership principles: 

1. Be a servant leader: Inspire, empower, & enable teams to execute
2. Always do what’s best for the business, not what’s politically popular. 
3. Let results do the talking

name: Chris Carson
title: Global AI Leader| Serial Entrepreneur | Founder & CEO of EchoTwin AI | Founder & Former CEO of Hayden AI
about:
As cities grow more complex, Chris Carson is leading a new era of urban intelligence. As the Founder and Global CEO of EchoTwin AI, he’s not just advancing technology—he’s transforming how cities function. His mission: to move cities beyond “smart” and toward something more powerful—cognitive, self-healing infrastructure.

Chris’s journey began with Hayden AI, where he developed vehicle-mounted, AI-powered systems that enforced traffic violations in real time. The technology was adopted by major U.S. cities and became a blueprint for mobile enforcement.

But enforcement alone wasn’t enough. It brought accountability but didn’t solve root issues. Cities needed more than detection—they needed awareness and autonomous action. That realization led to the founding of EchoTwin AI.

EchoTwin is Carson’s answer to fragmented urban systems. The platform uses edge AI, vision-language models (VLMs), and digital twins to turn everyday municipal fleets—like street sweepers and waste trucks—into mobile sensing units. These vehicles don’t just observe—they interpret and trigger automated workflows in real time.

From potholes and broken signs to overflowing bins and environmental hazards, EchoTwin detects and contextualizes issues and initiates resolution—autonomously. It’s not just visibility—it’s cognition. That’s what separates EchoTwin from traditional “smart city” solutions.

For Chris, this is about more than tools—it’s about redefining cities. Cognitive cities are resilient, responsive, and self-healing. EchoTwin enables this by merging siloed data into a unified, intelligent operational layer—the city’s digital nervous system.

With over 20 years of experience in AI, machine learning, and public-sector innovation, Chris has founded and scaled multiple successful tech companies. He combines deep technical knowledge with a relentless focus on execution and is recognized for delivering measurable impact.

A pragmatic operator, Chris champions Design Thinking, Lean Startup methods, and co-creation as keys to building scalable, lasting solutions. Under his leadership, EchoTwin has secured key government partnerships across the U.S. and Middle East and attracted top-tier investors aligned with his vision.

As EchoTwin expands globally, Chris’s goal is clear: the cities of tomorrow won’t just be smart—they’ll be cognitive, adaptive, and built to last.

name: Steve Hill
about:
Steve Hill is the retired President and CEO of The AEgis Technologies. In this role, he provided ongoing executive direction of a $130M+ annual revenue company with 380+ employees and its subsidiary business units in 10 locations throughout the US.  AEgis specializes in using modeling & simulation technology to support weapon systems development and war fighter exercise support and training.  One of the company's primary objectives is to use modeling & simulation to train our war fighters so they come home safely.  The company has particular technical expertise in Directed Energy, Satellite Communications, C4ISR, Virtual Reality and Cyber Security.  AEgis Technologies was acquired Arlington Capital Partners out of Washington, D.C. in late 2019.

Although Steve grew up an Army dependent in a variety of locations around the world, he considers the Huntsville, Alabama area to be home. Steve and his wife, Andi, have three adult children all of which were born deaf, have bilateral cochlear implants and use the Listening & Spoken Language (LSL) Communication Mode. Their children overcame the challenges from deafness to all graduate college - one with a Doctorate in Physical Therapy, one a professional Gunsmith with his own business, and one a current student in Physicians Assistant Graduate school.   Andi is a very active advocate and policy proponent for deaf/hard of hearing children and their families and the founder of The Center for Advancement of NextGen Deaf.  Steve enjoys working out, hiking, mountain biking, boating/wake surfing, and spending time with his family. Steve is the Board Chair for Lincoln Village Ministry and for the International Leadership Institute and a Board Member of BlueHalo, the Woolley Institute for Spoken Language Education (WISE) and Redstone Village.  Steve is on the President’s Advisory Council at UAH and a member of the Parents Advisory Board for Samford University.  He is also an active member of C12 – a Christian business peer advisory group. Steve and Andi volunteer or support Casa Aleluya (Guatemala), The Cornerstone Initiative, CRU, East-West Ministries, The Enrichment Center, Huntsville Botanical Gardens, His Hands Mission International (Honduras), Heartlight Ministries, Huntsville Hospital Pediatric Audiology Center, Lincoln Village Ministries, Mission to the World, Project 82, UAH Basketball, and the Woolley Institute for Spoken Language Education (WISE).

name: Amit Etkin
title: Founder and CEO at Alto Neuroscience | Professor (Psychiatry) at Stanford University
about:
Amit is the founder and CEO of Alto Neuroscience (NYSE: ANRO), a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company that integrates the biology of the patient into drug development to improve the lives of people with mental health conditions. Alto currently has four drugs in mid to late-stage clinical trials in various psychiatric conditions, all using biomarkers to identify likely treatment responders. In pioneering this precision psychiatry approach -- the right drug for the right patient at the right time -- Alto aims to deliver novel and more effective treatments in a field with little clinical innovation across decades.

Amit is trained as a psychiatrist and neuroscientist, and joined the Stanford faculty in 2010. As a tenured Professor, he became an international leader in the neuroscience of psychiatric disorders and their treatments. In recognition of the influence of his ideas and work, Amit received the most competitive and prestigious NIH grant – the Director’s Pioneer Award – the first one given in clinical psychiatry. He has also consistently ranked in the top 0.1% of researchers by citations.  

Amit brings broad-based scientific and programmatic leadership and a compelling vision for connecting scientific discovery to pragmatic clinical and business goals. He has a proven track record of success in publication in the highest-impact journals, raising extensive public and private funding, and managing a large and diverse team of scientists, clinicians and engineers towards a shared scientific vision. His training and experience span from molecular biology, having done his PhD with Nobel Laureate Eric Kandel, through to human clinical and neuroscience studies, machine learning, and clinical trials – a breadth and perspective critical to the innovation Alto is bringing to precision psychiatry.

about:
Sid Sheth is an experienced entrepreneur, business builder and executive in the semiconductor industry having managed businesses spanning processors and connectivity for cloud, telecom, wireless infrastructure and enterprise. In 2001, Mr. Sheth was a founding team member of Aeluros, a mixed-signal networking IC company, where he held global marketing responsibility, until its successful acquisition by NetLogic in 2007. 

Mr. Sheth also spent many years at Intel Corp, where he held engineering and management positions in the Pentium microprocessor and network processor groups.

Harry Kargman is the founder and CEO of Kargo, the leading mobile brand advertising marketplace.  Harry was named an EY Entrepreneur of the Year in 2016. Under his leadership over the last thirteen years, Harry has transformed Kargo from a small start-up into one of the advertising industry’s fastest- growing and most innovative technology companies — announced as an Inc. 500 winner in 2015.  Harry sits on the Advertising Council Board of Directors.

Kargo’s technology can be found on more than 300 of the largest media company properties – from The New York Times to Hearst, NBC to Viacom, Scripps to Turner, CNN to Fox, Time, Inc. to Vice and many more– and its technology powers the campaigns of more than 200 of the most influential consumer brands.

Kargo has pioneered unique media formats and data across publishers to help serve the right advertising and creative formats to the right user.  Kargo has been recognized with some of highest honors in the digital advertising industry, including more than 7 Mobi and OMMA awards for creative innovation.

He is a frequent speaker and panelist at CES, IAB, Advertising Week, Websummit, Cannes and other advertising and technology conferences, and has been featured in The New York Times, The Today Show, AdAge, Bloomberg, Fox Business, The Wall Street Journal, NPR and dozens of other media outlets. 

Harry graduated with honors from Harvard College, where he is now an advisor to young entrepreneurs through the Harvard Innovation Lab.  He lives in New York City with his wife and three children.

As a global speaker and thought leader, Senderoff is a passionate advocate for wellness and compassionate leadership, championing a human-centered approach to business through the practice and study of mindfulness and quantum healing.

name: Barbara Tallent
title: Internet optimist - Co-founder/CEO Atsign
about:
My LinkedIn account was recently hacked and all my profile data was deleted, I will reassemble it when I get the time. Unfortunately LinkedIn does not have an option to restore this data, so please learn from me and back up your LinkedIn profile and all of your posts!

Security and privacy are very broken on the Internet. Atsign is fixing this problem in so many ways. Some day all social media will use cryptographic keys instead of usernames and passwords. Unfortunately we will suffer many more hacks and loss of our personal information until then.

Until I can reassemble my background, here is a quick summary:

My work history includes moving up the ranks on the technical/marketing side with product marketing positions at SGI and Altos computers. My leadership experience includes being the GM of the Z-Mail division of Network Computing Devices (which I sold to Netmanage), the CEO of Boldfish (enterprise email marketing software that I sold to Siebel), and Co-Founder of LiveBinders (educational software with over 1M registered users). As my friend and co-founder Kevin, used to say, I'm a start-up junkie - I just love building things.

We started Atsign in 2019 because we believed that the Internet could be far more secure, privacy-respecting, and safer place. It is a great privilege to work with our amazing team to help customers make their presence on the internet completely invisible to bad actors, and to allow them to sleep soundly at night.
speaking_engagements: Peaking Podcast interview discussing internet security and leadership; C Suite Scale Podcast interview on future of internet security; TECH(K)NOW Day talk on Building a Flat Organizational Structure; Podcast episode on data privacy as a human right; YouTube video on creating new online experiences

Dorit co-founded MDI with the mission to end suffering from drug-related morbidity and mortality. Outside of work, Dorit is a CrossFit enthusiast and loves to spend time with her girls, who like to make regular appearances in her Zoom meetings.

name: Jouko Ahvenainen
title: Entrepreneur, Business Executive, Investor, Author
about:
My dream and work is to create new things and get them to work in practice. I don’t take easy paths. I started my first business when I was 16. I have started a few startups, most of them being pioneers in their areas and built significant global business, invested in startups, and worked for global corporations where I did significant turnaround and new business projects.

I focus on data, analytics, fintech, and ML/AI solutions. I am very hands-on in my startups. I have vast experience of international business in Asia, Europe, and North America; I have lived and/or worked in Monaco, London, Austin, San Francisco, Singapore, Helsinki, Kuala Lumpur and Hong Kong. 

I hold three academic degrees in politics, finance and computer science, and a pilot license. I have written books and to publications (business, technology, geopolitics, military) and lived on three continents. I have never followed recommended career paths, and I believe broad knowledge and the right attitude is the way to get things happen and also make the world a better place.

I have a strong track record to pioneer new businesses and technology. I have been a founder in companies that have been first in the world to make social network analytics for marketing and risk management, equity crowdfunding (influencing on the US President and Congress to change regulation), vertical AI solution (personal data AI and geopolitics). 

I have often been the first one to get first customers in new countries and managed personally up to $40M annual sales. In corporations I started new business units, setup European operations for a US company, and made a total turnaround for an Asian joint-venture. I have also been an external expert for work groups of the EU Council, US government, MIT Enterprise Program, Vietnam Innovation Program and the Finnish Defence Forces.

My startups have also raised significant funding, but at the same time I always prefer strong business and revenue over fancy VC deal announcements. 

I plan to do unexpected things also in the future. 

I regularly speak about new technology and business in conferences and media including CNBC Squawk Box, SXSW, MWC, Drucker Forum and Horasis. I have been listed as a World Influencer in the Digital Industry and Fintech.

I hold an MBA from Aalto University and McCombs School of Business, at University of Texas, Austin and a M.Sc. from the School of Science, at Aalto University, and B.Soc.Sc. at the University of Helsinki.

Specialties: Serial-entrepreneur, data analytics, ML, AI, fintech, digital health.

As a physician, epidemiologist, biomedical engineer, scientist, and entrepreneur, I am optimizing healthcare by translating clinical needs into technical solutions. I am co-founder at Segmed, the fastest growing self-serve platform for diverse, high quality, de-identified medical imaging data. Previously, I led the clinical cardiovascular imaging research at Stanford Radiology.

My clinical experience in diagnostic radiology and research experience in the field of cardiovascular and chest imaging allow me to recognize medical shortcomings. While my technical background with a PhD (cum laude) in medical imaging allows me to solve these with adequate technical solutions.

I have leadership experience from active involvement in multiple (inter)national scientific organizations, co-directing educational courses, supervising >15 graduate students, and am co-founder of Segmed, a Y Combinator and StartX-backed company.

I am designated as a Fellow of the Society of Cardiovascular Computed Tomography (SCCT) and an active member of multiple European and North American clinical scientific societies. My work has amongst others been recognized with awards from the Radiological Society of North America, European Society of Radiology, Society of Thoracic Radiology, and European Society of Thoracic Imaging.

name: David Fano
title: Tech Founder & Career AI Leader | CEO of Teal | Building the AI That Helps People Navigate Their Careers
about:
I’ve worked with tens of thousands of professionals on their careers—whether as a hiring manager, senior executive, founder, or now through Teal, where we’ve helped over 3 million people grow their careers with confidence. From reviewing resumes to building hiring systems, I’ve seen every side of the job search—and I’m on a mission to make it more transparent, equitable, and empowering.

That’s why I started Teal in early 2020. We’re building a career growth platform that uses AI and modern technology to simplify the job search, personalize the experience, and give individuals the same tools companies use to manage talent. We’ve helped people land new roles, negotiate raises, and gain clarity in their career paths—at scale.

With over 20 years as a technology practitioner and entrepreneur, I’ve led across product and service businesses, from B2B enterprise to consumer applications. I co-founded CASE, later acquired by WeWork, where I held executive roles including Chief Product Officer and Chief Growth Officer. I helped scale global operations—opening over 2 million square feet of space per month, often at 60–80% occupancy—and built products and teams that touched every part of the business.

Throughout my career, I’ve built productivity tools, physical products, and large-scale consumer search experiences. I’ve hired thousands of people and shaped the policies and systems behind how companies build culture and grow talent.

Now, with Teal, I’m bringing that expertise to individuals. If you want practical, honest insights on job searching, resumes, and how AI is transforming the way we work—follow me here on LinkedIn.

title: CEO & Founder at Shiru, AI protein discovery for industrial applications | Partner at XFactor Ventures
about:
I’m an entrepreneur passionate about making the global food system sustainable. I founded the biotechnology startup Shiru to make delicious, nutritious, sustainable, and scalable ingredients so that all food companies on Earth -- from hot new brands to multinational incumbents -- can quickly develop plant-based products. 

Our team includes biochemists, data scientists, business development professionals and others who want to help solve the biggest threats facing humanity: global warming, biodiversity collapse, and our public health crisis. We share a mission and sense of urgency -- that’s why we raised money, hired a world-class team, built an R&D lab and released our ingredients catalog within 12 months… in the midst of a global pandemic.

In addition to my work as CEO and Founder of Shiru, I’m a mom, a 2019 graduate of Y Combinator, former Director of Food Chemistry at JUST, and a former summer associate for VC firm Lux Capital. I have a doctorate in protein engineering from New York University, a Masters of Science in Materials Engineering from Chalmers University, and a Bachelor of Science in Chemical Engineering with a minor in Biotechnology from McGill University.  

Ask me anything about: fundraising while pregnant, growing up in New York City, cheerleading, or Sweden. Be sure to check out our job openings at https://jobs.lever.co/shiru.

name: Alexandre (Alex) Hadade

He founded Eizo in 2009, which is a distributor of medical and advertising monitors and sold it after 4 years. Alexandre led the reinvention of his own business a few times. He is very innovative. He was chosen as one of the 20 most innovative people in Latin America by CNBC in 2011. He is part of YPO organization. He is very serious, dedicated, disciplined and committed to achieving his goals. He has a great ability to generate trust in relationships for its transparency and pragmatism. He's using all his executive experience, his entrepreneurial sense and relationships to develop his newest business in the USA: Birdie.

name: Daniel Haders II, Ph.D.
title: Healthcare Operator, Investor, BoD Member
location: San Diego County, California, United States
about:
Dr. Haders was recently named one of "The Top 50 Healthcare AI Entrepreneurs of 2025" and was featured by Bloomberg Intelligence in their "Vanguards of Healthcare" series. 

https://thegreatentrepreneurs.com/the-top-50-healthcare-ai-entrepreneurs-of-2025/ 
https://www.bloomberg.com/news/audio/2025-04-01/model-medicines-ai-drug-development-vanguards-of-health-care

He is the Co-Founder & CEO of Model Medicines, an AI-driven, human health company using AI to model chemistry and human biology. The company has built a pipeline of novel acting therapeutics, including the potential best-in-class, first-in-class MDL-001. Model Medicines has raised over $14M to date with backing from investors including 8VC, Friedman Bioventures, Irving Ventures, ParticleX & Thermopolis Partners. 

The company's recent accolades include being named: 
A Fierce Medtech "Fierce 15" company 
GEN's "Ten Companies to watch in AI Drug Discovery"
GreyB's "5 Innovative AI Drug Development Startups to Watch in 2025"

Prior to MM, Daniel launched a Digital Health Accelerator. Here, Daniel built an early-stage investment portfolio of 25+ Digital Healthcare companies w/, investment results that would place the portfolio in the top decile. During his tenure the accelerator was named one of the "Top Ten Global Digital Health Accelerators" & "The Best Accelerators & Incubators for FemTech Startups".  He also managed partnered accelerators w/ numerous countries & publicly traded companies incl'ing Enterprise Singapore, Canada and GE Healthcare.

Daniel has served as an Operating Partner in the Venture Capital Industry, where has advised on Digital Health portfolios, including companies such as MedCrypt & AppliedVR.

Dr. Haders has served as a Board Member or Observer at multiple companies including AppliedVR, Regenexx, Consano Biologics, & Model Medicines, & has served as a Faculty Member & Member of the Advisory Committee of the UCSD, Digital Health Certificate Program & is a Member of the BioMedX Oversight Committee at Columbia University Technology Ventures.

Prior to current roles, he held positions from Fellow to Senior Scientist to Co-Founder/CEO in the fields of medical devices, pharmaceuticals & nano-drug delivery. At LuxBio, Daniel helped develop LX214 from concept through a successful Phase I study. The LX214 program was further developed clinically by Sun Pharma & gained FDA approval under the name CEQUA in 2018.

Dr. Haders holds a BS & PhD in Biomedical Eng. & has been awarded multiple Fellowships for his scientific research by the NSF, DoE and others.

name: William Uppington
title: AI @ Snowflake (Ex-CEO TruEra - Observability for Generative & Predictive AI)
about:
I'm focused on helping companies maximize the performance and quality of their AI applications. At TruEra. We have created the first Full Lifecycle AI Observability software for Generative & Predictive AI applications by combining monitoring, testing, debugging/root cause analytics, AI explainability and responsible AI capabilities into a single solution. Based on research started by my co-founders at CMU 8+ years ago, TruEra has capabilities not available anywhere else.

AI has the power to transform every industry but actually building AI applications that can sustainably hit their organizational objectives is very difficult. AI applications can experience many types of problems: don't hit KPIs, non-optimal performance/quality, operational (e.g. can't explain or build trust), responsible AI (e.g. concerns around bias). LLM applications have created a new set of challenges including challenges around hallucinations and security/privacy. TruEra's mission is to solve these problems and "Ensure effective and trustworthy AI for everyone."

In my career, my focus has been on understanding new problems in the world and then bringing new technologies and products to market to solve these problems.  I like starting and growing new companies as a way to do this. I've built 8 products so far as the lead product manager or general manager and launched countless features/modules as part of this.  For 6 of these, I was playing a lead role in building them largely from scratch.  All of these have achieved multi-million dollar run rates. For 4 of these products, I not only led the building of the product but I played a lead role in securing the first set of customers and designing the go-to-market (i.e. sales and marketing approach). 

I have not done any of these things alone and have been fortunate to work with amazing colleagues and a part of great teams. I'm working with a fantastic team at Truera and we are looking for more of these people now!

Specialties: Artificial Intelligence (AI) - Machine Learning (ML) - Model Management - Model Intelligence - Search - Search Engine Marketing (SEM) - SEO - Internet marketing - Web Analytics - Social Networking - Social Media - SaaS software - Enterprise Software - Networking - Security.

Disciplines: Product Management - Product Marketing - Online Marketing - Positioning - Pricing - B2B Marketing - PR/AR - Sales - Account Management - General Management - anything that needs to get done

name: Nick Walton
title: CEO of Latitude | Built AI Dungeon (8M+ downloads) | Building Heroes: an AI RPG Engine that can bring any world to life
about:
I became hooked on two things: the creative freedom of D&D and the potential of AI to enhance games. When I combined them during a hackathon in 2019 the result was AI Dungeon.

From BYU's Perception, Control & Cognition lab to Aurora's autonomous vehicles, I kept seeing AI's potential to create new things. Then came AI Dungeon - one of the first commercial applications of GPT models. We grew so fast we hit a $20K server bill in week one. 

We had to shut it down, and within two days our community built an entire peer-to-peer network to bring it back online because they loved it so much.

That taught me something crucial: focus on giving value to users first, everything else follows.

After 6 years and 10+ AI game prototypes, we've discovered how to create experiences that current games can't touch:

- Dynamic worlds where your choices really matter
- Unique stories personalized to you
- Freedom to do anything you can imagine
- Characters that really feel alive

Think Minecraft meets D&D, powered by AI:

- Persistent worlds where your actions are remembered
- Deep progression systems giving you unique skills based on your choices
- Rich AI characters that truly live and respond
- Epic narratives that pit you against imposing odds

We're building the kind of game I dreamed about when first rolling D20s - where the only limit is your imagination.

- Created one of the first commercial GPT applications in 2019
- Pioneer in AI gaming - built one of the first commercial GPT applications in 2019
- Created AI Dungeon, reaching 8M+ downloads
- Worked on autonomous vehicles at Aurora
- Developed LLM-based game course with Together AI
- Led multiple innovations in AI/gaming fusion
- Built an engine that enables dynamic, persistent game worlds

Building the future of gaming at Latitude:
- Hiring senior AI & game engineers
- Early access to Heroes coming soon
- Follow for AI gaming insights

From text adventures to today's AI worlds - we're just getting started.

Building some exciting stuff in AI gaming - let’s connect!

name: Krista Carroll
title: Founder | CEO | Latitude
about:
As CEO of Latitude, Krista Carroll leads with humanity, authenticity, warmth and an unwavering dedication to excellence. Her rock-solid drive to be the best in the business is not just about providing great products and services; she’s also committed to running a company where Purpose Elevates Talent. She started Latitude in 2009 with her husband Jeremy at their kitchen table, founded in an urgent desire to work for a better world. Their shared ambition to provide food, water, and safety for women and children around the world is what motivates them, and in turn what motivates the entire Latitude team.

Krista is excited to prove that a different style of leadership can be incredibly effective, and to work like crazy to see Latitude’s vision implemented. She does that by applying her strengths in seeing opportunity & developing people to reach their potential.. She is naturally innovative because she doesn’t come from the agency world. Krista’s talent at using empathy to address the fears of clients and employees helps remove barriers to boldness and innovation. As a result, the Latitude team can be their best, and client loyalty follows.  

The CEO title for Krista stands for genuine relationship, dedication to excellence, taking calculated risks,  and being the rock for the team. She does it to be the best, because by being the best at what they do, Latitude will being able to partner in more meaningful ways with the global community and after donating more than $8M to global organizations, Krista is more energized than ever.

Latitude is a creative agency focused on designing brands and experiences for brands who dare to stand for something greater than business. Latitude's offices in Minneapolis and Portland support the growing list of global brands the company is serving.

name: Ross Booher
title: Chief Executive Officer at Latitude
about:
Ross Booher co-founded and is CEO of Latitude. He previously served as an equity partner in a corporate law firm.

While practicing law, Ross represented publicly-traded and large private corporate clients in complex litigation, investigations, compliance matters, and transactions, as well as start-up companies, individuals and non-profit organizations. He tried numerous bench and jury trials and served as lead counsel in criminal and internal investigations in Africa, Asia, and Europe. 

Ross’​s professional and civic roles have included serving as chairman of the Business Crimes and Compliance Practice Group of Lex Mundi and as chairman of the board of KIPP Academy Nashville, a public charter school for at risk children.

Ross was recognized as one of the Nashville Business Journal's 2019 "Most Admired CEOs and their Companies" and in the Nashville Post In Charge List of the “best-of-the-best” business, political and civic leaders in 2016-2025. He was also selected for the 2010 Nashville Business Journal’s “40 under 40” Business Leaders. Ross received the Tennessee Bar Association’s 2007-2008 Harris Gilbert Pro Bono Attorney of the Year award for the successful representation of a naval officer in a high-profile civil rights and whistleblower matter which resulted in investigations by the Inspectors General of both the U.S. Justice and Defense Departments, and investigations by U.S. Senator Charles Grassley of Iowa and the CBS News program “60 Minutes."

Before entering private practice, Ross served on active duty in the U.S. Navy as a Judge Advocate General’s Corps officer (JAG) throughout the Pacific, the Middle East and in Europe.

Ross received his undergraduate degree from Vanderbilt University and graduated summa cum laude from the University of Tennessee College of Law.

Taking a quick break from startups, he worked at NOAA and Google while earning his Harvard advanced degrees.

All his experience and education culminated in Ekkobar, his latest venture.  Ekkobar’s Social Decision Intelligence platform provides answers from social media to help entertainment and sports brands mitigate risk and increase revenue.  Internet Magazine called Rhys “the geek that can speak,” and he has proven it through this career as a published author and international speaker.

Rhys has a background in mathematics, computer science, data science, artificial intelligence, and business analytics, giving him a unique perspective and a powerful blend of technical and business skills. Aside from business, Rhys is a foster parent, an avid dog lover, and a volunteer for various non-profits.

name: Aydogan Ozcan
title: Chancellor's Professor at UCLA & HHMI Professor
about:
Dr. Ozcan is the Chancellor’s Professor and the Volgenau Chair for Engineering Innovation at UCLA and an HHMI Professor with the Howard Hughes Medical Institute, leading the Bio- and Nano-Photonics Laboratory at UCLA Electrical Engineering and Bioengineering Departments, and is also the Associate Director of the California NanoSystems Institute (CNSI) at UCLA. 

Dr. Ozcan is elected a Member of the National Academy of Engineering (NAE) and a Fellow of the National Academy of Inventors (NAI) and holds >85 issued/granted patents and >20 pending patent applications. Dr. Ozcan gave 100+ plenary/keynote talks and 500+ invited talks and is also the author of 1 book and the co-author of more than 1200 peer-reviewed publications in major scientific journals and conferences. In addition, Dr. Ozcan is the founder and a member of the Board of Directors of Lucendi Inc. and Holomic/Cellmic LLC, which was named a Technology Pioneer by The World Economic Forum in 2015. Mobile diagnostics product lines and related assets of Cellmic were acquired by NOW Diagnostics in 2018. Ozcan is also the Founder of Pictor Labs. He led the fundraising and formation of Pictor Labs - a spin-off from his UCLA lab - which reported the first demonstration of AI-based digital tissue staining and telepathology.

Dr. Ozcan received several awards, e.g., the Presidential Early Career Award for Scientists and Engineers, International Commission for Optics (ICO) Prize, Rahmi M. Koc Science Medal, Dennis Gabor Award (SPIE), Joseph Fraunhofer Award & Robert M. Burley Prize (Optica), SPIE Biophotonics Technology Innovator Award, Keith Terasaki Innovation Award, SPIE Early Career Achievement Award, ARO Young Investigator Award, NSF CAREER Award, NIH Director’s New Innovator Award, ONR Young Investigator Award, IEEE Photonics Society Young Investigator Award and Distinguished Lecturer Award, as well as MIT’s TR35 Award. Ozcan is also the recipient of the National Geographic Emerging Explorer Award, National Academy of Engineering The Grainger Foundation Frontiers of Engineering Award, Popular Science Brilliant 10 Award, Gates Foundation Grand Challenges Award, Popular Mechanics Breakthrough Award, Netexplorateur Award, Microscopy Today Innovation Award, the Wireless Innovation Award (Vodafone Americas Foundation) and the Okawa Foundation Award.

Dr. Ozcan is elected Fellow of AAAS, SPIE, OSA, IEEE, AIMBE, RSC, APS and Guggenheim Foundation. Ozcan's CV:  
https://drive.google.com/file/d/162hTprALKUjRWyqKn7kuO1PRpMkJjl4r/view?usp=share_link

At Mango Sciences, our mission is to make cancer care more accessible and affordable for people across the developing world. With 4.5M newly diagnosed cancer patients across SE Asia & North Africa every year, the vast majority are unable to afford life saving targeted immunotherapies which are standard of care in the developed world.

We solve this problem by bringing the ecosystem of hospitals, life sciences and lenders together to enable risk-based financing for these life saving drugs. Patients pay for clinical outcomes which is made affordable by microfinancing.

Mango Sciences believes everyone across the globe should have access to life saving innovation.

name: Sinhwa Kang
title: HCI Research and Application Consultant for XR projects, Co-Founder at SOAP Health
about:
I am a human-computer interaction research and application consultant for Extended Reality (XR) projects and a co-founder at SOAP Health. I worked as a communication scientist and researcher at the University of Southern California’s Institute for Creative Technologies (USC ICT) for almost 12 years by working for the Mixed Reality (MxR) Group, the Medical Virtual Reality (MedVR) Group, and the Computational Emotion Group. My research focused on affective human-agent interaction in social and psychotherapeutic interactions. I adopted interdisciplinary theoretical and methodological approaches to my research, specifically in social and clinical psychological contexts. 

I have participated in projects funded by the National Science Foundation and the US military. I modeled a novel approach to explore interactants' perceptions of co-presence and the medium of the interaction. This included integrating virtual humans into emotionally engaging computer-mediated interactions. Using the approach, I researched investigating virtual humans as virtual counselors in mixed-reality settings including smartphone applications. I appeared in The New York Times with my work (“In Cybertherapy, Avatars Assist With Healing”) and received the "New Investigator Award" for a presentation of outstanding research quality at the CyberTherapy & CyberPsychology conference.

I obtained an M.Sc. from the Georgia Institute of Technology in Atlanta, Georgia, and a Ph.D. from the Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute in Troy, New York, majoring in Communication with a concentration in Human-Computer Interaction. Before coming to the US, I worked in the industry including Samsung, researching and developing web applications for online communities, marketing, and industrial training in Seoul, Korea where I earned my bachelor's degree from Ewha Womans University.

name: Jouko Ahvenainen
title: Entrepreneur, Business Executive, Investor, Author
about:
My dream and work is to create new things and get them to work in practice. I don’t take easy paths. I started my first business when I was 16. I have started a few startups, most of them being pioneers in their areas and built significant global business, invested in startups, and worked for global corporations where I did significant turnaround and new business projects.

I focus on data, analytics, fintech, and ML/AI solutions. I am very hands-on in my startups. I have vast experience of international business in Asia, Europe, and North America; I have lived and/or worked in Monaco, London, Austin, San Francisco, Singapore, Helsinki, Kuala Lumpur and Hong Kong. 

I hold three academic degrees in politics, finance and computer science, and a pilot license. I have written books and to publications (business, technology, geopolitics, military) and lived on three continents. I have never followed recommended career paths, and I believe broad knowledge and the right attitude is the way to get things happen and also make the world a better place.

I have a strong track record to pioneer new businesses and technology. I have been a founder in companies that have been first in the world to make social network analytics for marketing and risk management, equity crowdfunding (influencing on the US President and Congress to change regulation), vertical AI solution (personal data AI and geopolitics). 

I have often been the first one to get first customers in new countries and managed personally up to $40M annual sales. In corporations I started new business units, setup European operations for a US company, and made a total turnaround for an Asian joint-venture. I have also been an external expert for work groups of the EU Council, US government, MIT Enterprise Program, Vietnam Innovation Program and the Finnish Defence Forces.

My startups have also raised significant funding, but at the same time I always prefer strong business and revenue over fancy VC deal announcements. 

I plan to do unexpected things also in the future. 

I regularly speak about new technology and business in conferences and media including CNBC Squawk Box, SXSW, MWC, Drucker Forum and Horasis. I have been listed as a World Influencer in the Digital Industry and Fintech.

I hold an MBA from Aalto University and McCombs School of Business, at University of Texas, Austin and a M.Sc. from the School of Science, at Aalto University, and B.Soc.Sc. at the University of Helsinki.

Specialties: Serial-entrepreneur, data analytics, ML, AI, fintech, digital health.

name: Josh Sullivan
title: Investor, serial entrepreneur, startup mentor, best-selling author and beginner surfer
about:
Josh Sullivan, Ph.D., is an American investor, serial entrepreneur, startup mentor, best-selling author and beginner surfer. 

Josh is the Managing Director of alani capital, investing in visionary entrepreneurs and diverse founders in early-stage startups for angel, pre-seed and seed rounds. 

Previously, Josh was the co-founder and former CEO of Modzy, the enterprise AI platform to deploy and scale production machine learning. He founded and led the worldwide AI practice at Booz Allen, as EVP and Partner. He also led large technical programs in the National Security & Intelligence business. 

Josh authored best-selling AI book “Mathematical Corporation” with comment from Mark Fields, CEO Ford and Larry Bossidy, CEO Honeywell, and he is the co-author of the celebrated “Field Guide to Data Science”, now in the second edition. Early in his career, Josh co-founded a software & services startup and scaled the small business to a successful exit. Josh started his career in US Intelligence Community as an engineer. 

He is a frequent conference speaker with numerous articles in the Atlantic, CNBC, WSJ, HBR, and TechCrunch. Josh is a former corporate advisory board member MIT CSAIL, Purdue University, and the University of Maryland, and former Member of Center for New American Security (CNAS) Task Force on Artificial Intelligence and National Security.

name: Eric Wengrowski
title: Founder @steg.ai, PhD
about:
Dr. Eric Wengrowski is the CEO and Co-founder of Steg.AI. Before starting Steg, he focused on Computer Vision and Machine Learning research. He has a PhD in the Electrical & Computer Engineering from Rutgers University where his research adviser was Professor Kristin J. Dana.

His research interests include photographic steganography, computational photography & imaging, and deep learning.

In 2020, Eric was a post-doctoral researcher appointment at NYU in the Center for Cybersecurity where he collaborated with Nasir Memon and Pawel Korus.

Eric and Steg AI are the 2019 LDV Summit Entrepreneurial Computer Vision Challenge (ECVC) winner. Eric is a 2019 alum of the National Science Foundation Innovation Corps program.

In 2017, Eric was a research intern at Siemens Healthcare working on deep learning for medical imaging under the leadership of Dr. Bogdan Georgesc and Dr. Dorin Comaniciu.

In 2016, Eric interned at Kitware and worked on the DARPA-sponsored image forensics project Medifor, a collaboration with Dartmouth University, University of California Berkeley, and University of Albany. Eric worked under the leadership of Dr. Zhaohui Harry Sun and Dr. Anthony Hoogs.

In 2015, Eric interned at Microsoft Research in Redmond, WA with the Interactive Visual Media Group  lead by Dr. Richard Szeliski where he collaborated with Krishnan Ramnath, Dr. Neel Joshi, and Dr. Michael Cohen.

name: Preeti Bhargava
title: Co-Founder and CTO @ Arintra
about:
I am the co-founder and CTO of Arintra where we are building AI powered solutions to reduce administrative inefficiencies in US healthcare. If you would like to chat more or are interested in working with us, please reach out. 

I have a PhD in Computer Science from University of Maryland, College Park with several years of extensive research and industry work experience in Data Science, Big Data, Machine Learning and NLP.  I have been fortunate to have worked on different and versatile domains in my professional career and PhD including information extraction from social media, big data modeling, personalization and recommender systems, Internet of Things, location based systems, on-device and offline user modeling, and mobile systems. 

In my work, I have successfully worked on and incorporated several machine learning and natural language processing techniques in supervised, semi-supervised and unsupervised learning such as binary and multi-label classification, regression, matrix and tensor factorization, dimensionality reduction, association rules, stacked ensembles, clustering, outlier detection, Markov models etc. I relish participating in every step of the data science pipeline from modeling the problem, defining the metrics, cleaning unstructured data, feature engineering, designing and prototyping  machine learning algorithms as well as their productionization.

I have been awarded 2 patents have published 35+ peer-reviewed publications in several international conferences (WWW, IUI, EMNLP, ICDM, Mobiquitous, UbiComp etc.) and journals. I am a proud recipient of  the UMD Ann G Wylie dissertation fellowship, UMD Dean's fellowship, Palantir scholarship for Women in Technology, Grace Hopper Celebration of Women in Computing Scholarship and several conference travel grants.

name: Austin Harrison
title: CEO
about:
Austin is the CEO of industry-leading marketing attribution company Northbeam. He began his software career in audience analysis, helping to build the first audience panel for NetRatings, which was later acquired by Nielsen in 2007 for $327M. He then moved his focus to digital marketing, believing that AI & machine learning could revolutionize marketing attribution. Together with his co-founder Dan Huang, he built Northbeam into the leading marketing attribution platform. For media buyers and business executives who need to know exactly how their marketing spend is performing – and how to improve it – Northbeam is their greatest resource, leveraging the industry’s best first-party data with unrivaled visibility across all critical marketing platforms.

Austin also makes comics and animation at Noble Transmission. There he’s launched original IP including “Wild Blue Yonder,” which was selected by the American Library (YALSA) as one of the 100 Great Graphic Novels for Teens.

name: Terralynn Forsyth
title: AI Product Leader | Founder | AI for Extending Human Agency
about:
Terralynn is a founder and product leader building AI products to extend human agency with +10 years experience across entrepreneurship, 0 to 1 product building, and AI systems (NLP, recommenders, data pipelines, LLMs, and agentic AI).

She most recently served as a Cofounder and CPO at FutureFit AI, a company using AI to streamline workforce transitions and operations at scale. In this role, she led product and data teams during the growth stage of the company's two flagship products: Pathways, a platform for demand-driven workforce ecosystems, and Career Copilot, an agent-based AI career assistant delivering personalized career guidance to workforces, serving over 100,000 job seekers in their job transitions.

Previously, Terralynn was FutureFit AI's Head of Data, where she led generative AI strategy, data sourcing and integrations, and the application of natural language processing in product recommender systems. As the founding Head of Product, she also spearheaded the company’s early data, product, and design initiatives, including a complete redesign and rebuild of its platform. FutureFit AI has garnered support from leading investors such as JP Morgan, Techstars, and Acumen, and its work has been recognized by the World Economic Forum, Harvard Business Review, SHRM, World Government Summit, and a $1M Future of Work Prize.

Terralynn has contributed to global thought leadership on the future of work and skills with organizations such as the OECD, World Economic Forum, and Canadian Council for Youth Prosperity. Her insights have been featured in The Economist, Financial Times, BNN Bloomberg, and BBC.

Terralynn is a c100 Fellow, NextAI 2019 Cofounder, and contributes to committees on topics such as labour market information, data practices, and AI.

She is now focused on AI agents, fractional AI product advisory / leadership, and emerging patterns of agentic UI / UX, product design, and hybrid work with AI. Other curiosities include science fiction, cognitive science, and fine tuning the seminomadic lifestyle.

name: Francesco D'Orazio
title: 3x Founder in data, AI, analytics, TEDx Speaker, McLuhan Fellow, Ph.D. Social Science
about:
Product and research leader, specialised in AI, data, Internet culture and the evolution of online audiences. I enjoy building products at the intersection of AI, data visualization and behavioural science to figure out what audiences think and how culture is shifting.

I co-founded audience intelligence firm Pulsar and I'm currently CEO having served as Vice President of Product and Research for the previous 5 years. I'm also one of the co-founders of the Visual Social Media Lab, an industry-academia think tank specialised on studying the impact of online visual languages on society. 

My work focusses on designing systems and research frameworks that help analyze digital audience signals (social, search, web) to understand cultures, behaviours and perceptions at scale. Most of my research focusses on virality, fandoms, social influence, public opinion and cultural trends.

Over the past ten years I have been running innovation programmes for tech startups, agencies and public organisations delivering a wide range of data-driven products and experiences for the social media, research, gaming and adtech industries.

I have a PhD in Social Sciences and Digital Media (2004-2007) from Università degli Studi di Roma ‘La Sapienza’ and a fellowship at the McLuhan Program in Culture and Technology at the University of Toronto where my research focused on Immersive Media, the evolution of Audiences and the rise of Social Media.

I do a fair bit of public speaking and I have contributed to research, innovation and technology conferences such as SXSW, Strata, DMWF, The Next Web, TMRE, IIEX, International Journalism Festival, TedX, Big Data Week, Social Media Week, Social Data Week, WARC, MRS, Esomar, Virtual Worlds Forum, World Business Forum. 

My work has been featured in the likes of BBC, Guardian, CNN, Forbes, The Independent, Daily Mail, Corriere Della Sera, Sole 24 Ore, Mashable, Gigaom, Business Insider etc. oh and on Commander Hadfield's Twitter feed.

Specialties: Innovation, Futures, Product Management, Social Data, Data Visualization, Social Media Research, User experience, Immersive Media.

name: Robert Herman, MD, PhD
title: Founding CMO at PMcardio - AI that reads ECGs by Powerful Medical | Cardiovascular Care-Coordination Platform for Health Systems
location: New York, New York, United States
about:
Short: Robert Herman, MD, PhD is a physician-scientist and founding Chief Medical Officer of Powerful Medical. His CE-certified AI ECG platform, PMcardio, enables more than 50-thousand monthly active clinicians to interpret over 4 million ECGs each year, covering 40+ cardiac conditions. Backed by $50 million in non-dilutive funding and an FDA Breakthrough Device Designation for its STEMI model, Dr Herman leads multinational AI-cardiology trials and was named to Forbes Europe 30 Under 30 (Science & Health) in 2024.

---

Long: Robert Herman, MD, PhD is a physician-scientist at the forefront of cardiovascular innovation, devoted to the development, validation and real-world clinical implementation of AI models that accelerate the detection and management of heart disease. He is the founding Chief Medical Officer of Powerful Medical, an MDR-certified medical-device company that equips first-medical-contact healthcare professionals with AI-powered tools for real-time cardiovascular diagnostics and decision support.

Dr Herman earned his medical degree from Sigmund Freud University in Vienna and completed his PhD through CardioPath at the University of Naples Federico II (Italy), where he specialized in AI-enabled outcome prediction for cardiovascular patients. He completed clinical and research training at Wilhelminenspital (Austria), National Institute of Cardiovascular Diseases (Slovakia) and serves as a clinical researcher at the Cardiovascular Center Aalst in Belgium.

At Powerful Medical he leads the clinical development and validation of PMcardio, a CE Class IIb Software-as-a-Medical-Device care-coordination platform enabling more than 50k monthly active clinicians to interpret over 4 million ECGs each year, covering 40+ cardiac conditions. He also spearheaded the development and validation of the STEMI AI ECG model, which received FDA Breakthrough Device Designation for accelerating diagnosis and treatment of life-threatening acute myocardial infarction.

Dr Herman has secured more than $50 million in non-dilutive funding, through EIC Accelerator and the IPCEI Tech4Cure Programme, to advance the development and global implementation of AI in cardiology. In 2024 he was named to the Forbes Europe 30 Under 30 list (Science & Health) for his pioneering work in AI-driven digital health.

He currently steers several multinational clinical trials assessing the real-world deployment of AI in cardiology and has served on the Research, Digital & Innovation Committee of the EAPCI under the European Society of Cardiology.

name: Fabiana Clemente
title: Building LLM & GenAI-Powered Data Solutions | Synthetic Data & Multi-Modal AI | OSS Contributor & Public Speaker @YData
about:
I’m passionate about building AI that actually works in the real world — and I believe that starts with better data.

At YData, I’ve spent the last few years focused on solving one of the most overlooked challenges in machine learning: data quality. From synthetic data generation using generative models and LLMs to building tools that help teams profile and improve structured, unstructured, and multi-modal datasets, my goal has always been the same — to help data scientists build more reliable and effective AI systems.

I’ve had the chance to lead the development of our platform, contribute to open-source projects like ydata-profiling, and speak at conferences like PyData and ODSC — but what drives me most is creating tools that make life easier for data teams.

As a founding member of the Data-Centric AI Community, I’m also involved in sharing best practices and pushing for a shift in how the industry thinks about data in AI. I come from a background in applied math, forecasting, and machine learning, and I try to bring a hands-on, practical mindset to everything I do — whether it’s writing code, mentoring a team, or talking with users.

If you’re working on problems around data quality, generative AI, or responsible ML, I’d love to connect.

The creator economy is UNDER-hyped and will be far bigger than the wildest estimates.

Today, independent creators can already compete head to head with the giants by leveraging platforms: marketing & community building platforms (YouTube, TikTok, Instagram), e-commerce platforms (Shopify, Squarespace), financing platforms (Spotter, OpenSea, Patreon), talent platforms (Upwork, Fiverr). There are hundreds of niche platforms empowering independent creators and freelancers to make a living or create a sizable enterprise pursuing their passions. 

And with emerging GenAI, creators will be able to experience Exponential Creativity, competing even better than ever before.

As a result, for the first time in a hundred years, we now see a reversal and momentum shift back to small businesses. They aren't local in every town, but niche creators building global communities and selling products globally.

And its Day One. We predict there will be 500 million creators in 2029. 1 in 6 jobs will be a creator or someone working for them.

In 2029, the creator economy will become the global economy. What we watch and buy will be determined largely by creators.

Everything we know about how things are watched, marketed and sold will change.

Want to ride the wave? DM me

I’m the founder and CEO of Archipelo, where we’re creating a new category: Developer Security Posture Management (DevSPM).

Our mission is simple: Secure the software supply chain at its true origin—the developer and the AI systems writing the code.

Our platform integrates across the SDLC to surface real-time behavioral and risk signals—linking developer activity (human and AI), AI-generated code, and organizational risk.

We’ve filed patents for a new security layer:

* Developer Security Posture Management (DevSPM)
* Developer SIEM (DevSIEM)
* Developer Detection & Response (DevDR)
* Developer Posture & Prediction Engine (DevPPE)

I bring 20+ years across technology, software, cybersecurity, AI, cloud, infrastructure, and product strategy—with a JD from Berkeley and battle-tested leadership experience.

I’m also authoring Provenant, a sci-if tech-thriller exploring a future timeline when the vast majority of code is written by autonomous systems and AI—with human governance and the risks and implications for humanity in the age of systematic digital automation underpinning all infrastructure.

If you’re building in cybersecurity, AI, DevSecOps, or working toward creating more secure AI futures—I’d love to connect.

name: Corten Singer
title: Co-Founder & President at Augmental | Forbes 30 Under 30 in Social Impact
about:
Corten Singer is the cofounder of Augmental, which just recently launched the MouthPad, a bluetooth-enabled intraoral interface for hands-free control of your computer, smartphone & tablet.
Corten is enthusiastic about interactive device design and its ability to bridge the gap between the digital world and the physical, leveraging the power of computing to tackle some of our toughest physical challenges. He is especially passionate about assistive technology and loves working closely with individuals to design custom interfaces that increase independence and improve quality of life.

Corten completed his undergraduate studies at UC Berkeley in Computer Science & Cognitive Science. He continued his career in assistive tech while working for Microsoft Research and earning his Masters of Science at UC Berkeley in EECS, during which he developed novel eye-tracking interfaces to navigate power wheelchairs when the use of hands is not possible. Most recently, he cofounded Augmental, whose first product is a bluetooth mouse that is worn in the mouth and leverages the dexterity of the tongue to control one’s bluetooth-enabled devices.

name: Tomás Vega
title: Co-Founder & CEO at Augmental | MIT Media Lab | Forbes 30 Under 30
about: Tomás is passionate about developing assistive technologies, but more generally, he wants to design the human of the future (he wants to be a Cyborg!) - to create new and extend existing human sensory, motor, and cognitive abilities in order to enhance human performance beyond natural baseline. For this, he is developing new input and output interfaces to increase the bandwidth between humans and computers. Using these augmentative devices, he hopes to learn how the brain structurally and functionally reorganizes to accommodate new synthetic senses, control capabilities, and cognitive prostheses. He is interested in how neural plasticity can be exploited, how humans learn and encode information, and how perception can be affected (and possibly engineered!) at a conscious and subconscious level. He holds a double-major in Computer Science and Cognitive Science from UC Berkeley, and a Master's in Media Arts and Sciences from the MIT Media Lab.

name: Manuel Schönfeld
title: Chief Executive Officer at PowerX
about:
Manuel is a successful founder and the former CEO of PowerX, a hardware-enabled AI company on a mission to combat climate change. PowerX analyzes the energy signatures of equipment to create digital twins—unlocking energy savings, predictive maintenance, and AI-powered automation at the edge. The company deployed thousands of units to reduce energy and water use for some of the world’s leading brands and was acquired by Qu POS, Inc. in 2024.

Under Manuel’s leadership, PowerX was named one of Y Combinator’s Top 10 Companies of 2023 and backed by top-tier investors.

Before founding PowerX, Manuel worked at McKinsey & Company, advising governments and global companies on cutting-edge energy strategies—ranging from hydrogen-to-chemicals to power-to-X and solar-to-cooling. His work spanned six continents and helped shape large-scale decarbonization initiatives.

Earlier in his career, Manuel served as a consultant at the World Bank, where he was lead author on two books about intelligence and work readiness testing, with citations in global publications including the World Development Report 2018 (United Nations). He also worked at Morgan Stanley in Hong Kong, focusing on renewable energy investments and sovereign risk, and advised the Ministry of Labor in Saudi Arabia on workforce policy reform.

Manuel was a McCloy Scholar at Harvard University, receiving Germany’s most prestigious public service scholarship. He also earned the Van Beek Scholarship at Wharton, was a Haniel and Studienstiftung des deutschen Volkes scholar, and graduated with the highest GPA in the history of the Rotterdam School of Management. He pursued additional studies in Chinese, data science, and development economics at Heidelberg University and elsewhere.

His career has taken him across more than 100 countries, including Somalia, Saudi Arabia, China, India, and Germany where he served as CIO of a global humanitarian organization and built data systems to support large-scale aid and development programs.

about:
As CEO of Prospero.ai, I’m leading a fintech company on a mission to democratize Wall Street-level intelligence. We use cutting-edge AI—developed in partnership with NYU and refined over a decade—to deliver market-tested signals that empower both everyday investors and professionals. As of June 2nd, our free 2025 Newsletter Picks have outperformed the market by 120% annualized, 77% in 2024 and ~50% in 2023 and 2022. We also maintain remarkably consistent win rates against SPY, ranging between 58% and 61%. Over the years, our tools have helped many improve their financial futures.

I started in finance by teaching myself accounting to land a hedge fund job at 17. Since 2011, I’ve built predictive models across corporate bond demand, equity index additions, real estate pricing, and loan risk—often applying these methods to niche areas just for fun, from sports analytics to health-tracking motion models.

Prospero is the culmination of my life’s work: making elite financial tools accessible to all. I believe AI can be the great equalizer—and I'm passionate about building systems that prove it.

Outside of Prospero, I serve on the Fast Company Impact Council, a collective of creative leaders working on the most important opportunities and challenges in business. I'm also proud to be a Fellow at AI Circle, joining peers from OpenAI, NVIDIA, Anthropic, Meta, Cohere, and Perplexity in shaping the future of responsible, high-impact AI.

Previously, I was CEO of Instadat, an AI company focused on B2B predictive analytics primarily in the Financial Services space. 

Let’s connect—especially if you’re building at the frontier of AI, fintech, or believe in shifting power back to the individual investor.

name: Victor Velculescu
title: Professor, Johns Hopkins University School of Medicine | Founder, DELFI Diagnostics
about: Dr. Velculescu is internationally known for his discoveries in genomics and cancer research.  He led the first genome-wide sequence analysis of human cancers, identifying key genes and pathways dysregulated in tumorigenesis.  He developed methods for global gene expression analyses and coined the word “transcriptome" to describe the patterns that could now obtained in cancer and other cells.  These analyses identified a variety of genes not previously known to be involved in neoplasia, including PIK3CA as one of the most highly mutated genes in human cancer. These efforts have led to new FDA approved therapies and diagnostic tests widely used for cancer patients.  More recently, his group has invented non-invasive machine learning blood tests for early cancer detection.  These discoveries provide new paradigms for our understanding of human cancer that have benefited patients worldwide.

name: Corey Jaskolski
title: CEO at RAIC Labs (formerly Synthetaic) where we are fast-tracking the world’s transition to practical AI
about:
Corey Jaskolski is a National Geographic Fellow, explorer, and entrepreneur. Leveraging his expertise in deep AI and sensors, Corey has developed and deployed technologies for exploration and conservation missions in some of the world’s most beautiful and unforgiving environments. 

Corey is the founder and CEO of Synthetaic. Synthetaic is the end-to-end AI company. We build high-performing AI solutions in minutes, not months. Our flagship technology, RAIC (Rapid Automatic Image Categorization), eliminates the need for time-intensive human labeling or expensive labeled data troves. By automating the analysis of large, unstructured, datasets, RAIC offers instant detection of anything, at scale.

Jaskolski's work with National Geographic has taken him to all seven continents on projects like scuba diving among the icebergs in Antarctica, descending 12,500 feet below the ocean’s surface in a three-person submarine to explore the Titanic, and leading a helicopter-based effort to produce a high resolution aerial LIDAR map of the Nepalese side of Everest. His work often appears in National Geographic Magazine, online, in television specials on PBS and the National Geographic Channels, in scientific journals, and in international magazines. 

Jaskolski has also led technical projects for clients including NASA, the US Special Forces (SOCOM), Defense Advanced Research Agency (DARPA), and many US Army and Navy Research Laboratories.

Corey is the recipient of the 2020 Rolex National Geographic Explorer of the Year Award for his past and current accomplishments and innovations to advance conservation, anti-poaching security, and exploration.

Beyond his explorer and entrepreneurial work, Jaskolski serves as a member of the board of directors at the Milwaukee Public Museum.

I believe that the future of this industry lies in bridging the gap between traditional practices and the advanced capabilities that modern technology offers.

My latest venture, Aidium, is a highly customizable mortgage CRM and business intelligence platform that leverages AI-driven predictive analytics, robust data reporting, and intelligent automation to drive loan volume, enhance business decisions, and bridge the gap between loan officers and enterprises.

title: CEO & Co-Founder of Quark.ai, Technology and product guy, Informatica, Interval Research, Alchemist Accelerator, Bay Area IIT Startups
about:
I am a technologist, entrepreneur, corporate executive and investor.  For more than two decades, I have been among the foremost innovators at the intersection of Deep Learning, NLP and Computer Vision; data analytics and integration; and mobility and eCommerce. 

I have productized, developed and positioned multiple products designed to define and ultimately accelerate the growth of emerging technology markets. I am currently the co-founder and CEO of Quark.ai, an Autonomous Support platform that interprets customer issues to recommend resolutions automatically, skyrocketing agent productivity and customer experience.  Prior to this, I was the founder of StyleChat, the developers of digital try-on technology for the fashion and online commerce space. 

Mr. Sen was one of the founding team (employee #5) of Informatica Corporation, the worldwide leaders in data integration technology.  Informatica went public in 1999 and traded on Nasdaq until 2015, when it was acquired by private equity firm, Premira.  He also co-founded as CTO the first start-up spin off from Interval Research, Microsoft co-founder Paul Allen's research think tank.

He is also currently a CEO Coach-Mentor-Judge for the Alchemist Accelerator, a Mentor for the Bay Area IIT Startups, and is on the Advisory Board of WeMax Innovation Capital.

The co-author of "RFID for Energy & Utility Industries”, a bestselling book published by PennWell Publishers, Mr. Sen holds a BS in Electronics Engineering from the Indian Institute of Technology, Kharagpur.  A jazz, cooking and hiking enthusiast, he lives in Silicon Valley with his wife and two daughters.

name: Harsha K Rajasimha
title: Reimagining the Clinical Trials Infrastructure to Deliver Dramatic Efficiency for the AI era
about:
Harsha K Rajasimha, Ph.D., is a serial entrepreneur, scientist, patient advocate, and philanthropist. Harsha is Founder and CEO of Jeeva Clinical Trials Inc.(https://jeevatrials.com) a AI-driven unified platform for sponsors to execute modern clinical trials with efficiency and universal accessibility. Harsha serves as the founder chairperson of the Indo US Organization for Rare Diseases (https://indousrare.org), where he is forging a new era of cross-border cooperation among various stakeholders of rare diseases in the US, India, and globally by convening the annual Indo US bridging RARE Summit (https://summit.indousrare.org) and the Abbey Meyers Khushi Bridging RARE Awards Gala. 
Harsha’s 20 years of experience in precision medicine data research spans academia, federally funded research, healthcare and life science consulting, and multiple startups. Harsha made bold career moves after losing a newborn child to a rare congenital disease in 2012 and his younger brother with juvenile diabetes in 2017. He decided to apply his years of postdoctoral training at NIH and FDA to combat rare diseases. At Jeeva, Harsha leads the development of a unified software platform for efficient clinical trials for rare and common conditions that are universally accessible. He knew that technology is not the limiting factor and that patient-centered design guided by stakeholder needs and regulatory requirements would be critical ingredients of the continuously learning digital platform. By digitizing and automating manual repetitive tasks and reducing the logistical burdens on patients and study teams by over 70%, Jeeva accelerates the process of bringing new medicines or vaccines to diverse patients who need them anywhere by over 3x faster.
Harsha maintains academic affiliation at George Mason University since 2012 and has authored 17+ publications, book chapters, and patents. Harsha’s work has been recognized by Lead India Foundation 2020 Award for leadership and outstanding achievement in rare diseases, a travel award to join the NGO Committee on Rare Diseases at the United Nations headquarters, New York City in Feb 2019, NTT DATA Healthcare Life Sciences Silver award for outstanding achievement 2017, Sanofi Genzyme patient advocacy leadership award 2016, Bioscience company of the year 2014, NEI director’s innovation award 2012 for building their genomics data infrastructure.  Harsha earned his M.S. in Computer Science (2004) and Ph.D. in Genetics, Bioinformatics and Computational Biology (2007) from Virginia Tech.

name: Denise Hummel
title: Marshall Goldsmith's 100 Coaches (Start-Up to Enterprise), former EY Principal, SaaS Founder, Board Member and Mediterranean Sailing Vlogger
about:
I am retired, enjoying producing content on my Youtube channel @MedSailor and cruising the Mediterranean with my wonderful husband.

While working, I was nominated Microsoft M12 Female Founder and loved to work at the intersection of behavior change, technology and people impact. 

 With over 90,000 Linkedin members following her, she has been endorsed by Marshall Goldsmith as "a world leader in leveraging technology to sustain and scale transformation." She is the Founder and CEO of Rev Solutions Global, LLC which has incorporated the brands known as RevWork, RevMyLife and Lead Inclusively. All three brands utilize the SaaS technology she created, focused on human behavior change. Principle products produced on the platform include  Addiction Recovery Virtual Coach, Oncology Companion, Eating Disorder Virtual Coach, Assisted Living Virtual Companion, Depression and Suicide Prevention Virtual Coach, Remote Teams Virtual Coach, the Innovation Virtual Coach and Sales Enablement Virtual Coach and the Inclusion Virtual Coach App. She is also a member Marshall Goldsmith's Legacy Team of 100 Coaches (chosen from over 16,000 applicants), a former member of the Board of Directors of the Healthcare Women's Association (HBA),  and the former Co-Chair of the Life Sciences Committee of Athena and the Co-Chair of Education for the National Diversity Council. 

Denise sold her first business, culture firm, Universal Consensus, LLC, to Ernst & Young, where she became a Principal in their Human Capital division.  There she led a team of 40 PhD's at EY's Innovation Center in Kerala, India to leverage technology to operationalize her I.P. in culture transformation. Prior to that she practiced employment law and international M&A as an attorney.  Denise has lead some of the most significant people integrations of the life sciences and tech world and also focuses on the challenges faced by pharma and biotech as they enter a phase of fierce competition and crowded markets.  She is a staunch advocate of women and historically disenfranchised persons.

She has led Ernst & Young’s Talent, Diversity, Innovation and Culture Transformation offerings; led Aon-Hewitt’s cross-cultural M&A integration; built Deloitte’s cross-cultural assessment and training program for Global Mobility.  She developed a breakthrough trademarked methodology, the Business Model of Intercultural Analysis (BMIA™), related to global expansion and optimization; and litigating (and winning) the first class action under the Americans With Disabilities Act.

name: Benoit Scherrer
title:
CEO and Co-Founder at Quantivly, 
Assistant Professor at Harvard Medical School, 
Senior Staff AI Scientist at Boston Children's Hospital
about:
My mission> Democratize access to medical imaging by removing the operational bottlenecks that slow radiology. As CEO & co-founder of Quantivly, I’m building an agentic-AI “air-traffic-control” layer so every scanner runs better, staff are freed to focus on care, and every patient is seen sooner.

Why it matters>
Interpretive AI is easing the traditional reading backlog, but idle scanners, scheduling gaps, and siloed workflows have become the new choke point. Quantivly automates the decisions that keep imaging moving—boosting throughput, shortening wait times, and letting clinicians devote more time to patients.

My path>
• Started coding at 12; youngest finalist in Prologin, France’s 36-hour national programming marathon, at 15
• B.Eng. Computer Science (ranked #2, 2004)
• M.S. Computer Vision (2005)
• Ph.D. Applied Mathematics (2009, “Best Ph.D.” award) for *AI agent-based* brain-MRI segmentation
• Post-doc, Computational Radiology Lab, Boston Children’s Hospital (2009)
• AI Scientist, Boston Children’s Hospital (2014)
• Assistant Professor of Radiology, Harvard Medical School (2018)
• 50+ peer-reviewed papers, multiple innovation awards, two granted U.S. patents, more pending.

The aha moment>
After 12 years in a leading pediatric radiology department, I realized we measure almost everything except the operations that determine access. Quantivly is the answer: real-time situational awareness, predictive orchestration, and autonomous agents that coordinate rooms, people, and equipment.

Let’s connect>
Always up for a conversation about AI, healthcare operations, or scaling deep-tech startups. If you’re working to improve patient care—or just enjoy discussing agentic systems—feel free to reach out.
