name: Brenda Stonecipher
title: Finance and business ops expert helping leaders achieve more.
about:
Every successful organization has a person in senior management who is that company’s trusted resource, who will always level with people, who is given the most challenging projects even when they don’t neatly fit into her job description because everyone knows she will manage them successfully, whom others come to for guidance, and who is a strategic thinker. I am that person.

I am inclined toward action, whether implementing a new billing system or rearranging the furniture in my living room. I believe that change is best accomplished using a thoughtful and transparent process. I am skilled at identifying the target, envisioning the pathway, and guiding the team to success. 

I am a CPA not because I revel in the details, but because I am a storyteller. The operational and financial data of a business, if deftly arranged, narrates the life of the organization - its past, present, and future. 

An effective communicator, I possess a knack for cogent writing, engaging presentations, and the exceptional ability to listen more than I speak. As a manager, I maintain an open door to my direct reports and others who seeks my advice and counsel.

I am the founder and principal of Stonecipher Consulting Group, where I work to strengthen and support nonprofit organizations that are struggling with financial, operational, and strategic challenges and who want to stay at the forefront of their industry. 

I am the doyenne of dinner parties, competitive in my spin class, a trekker who drags her beloved golden retriever on the journey, a college hockey devotee, a political junkie who reads five news sites before breakfast, a globetrotter who loves the process of planning a trip almost as much as the travel itself, and I can do anything in heels. 

I have an MBA and BA from the University of Washington and I am a CPA. 

I’m always interested in hearing from former colleagues, managers, or others who want to connect – contact me!

He is the CEO of Carey International, the world's leading provider of chauffeured services and ground transportation logistics management. Prior to Carey, he was CEO of Mogul Hospitality, he led a VC-backed firm named one of the world’s top 30 travel tech startups. Mogul launched the first AI-driven human capital marketplace for hospitality, used by 800+ properties and 7 major brands. 

Previously, Alexander was CEO of Asia based Cachet Hotels & Resorts, pioneering sustainability including China's first carbon-neutral hotels and celebrity chef-driven restaurants. As CEO, he raised four rounds of capital, executed 15 hotel management deals, acquired $300 million dollars of luxury hotel assets across Asia and the Americas and built a proprietary booking engine. 

Earlier, he held senior executive roles reporting to the CEOs of Starwood Hotels and Resorts, Hilton Worldwide, and Caesars Entertainment. At Hilton, he restructured a $2 billion dollar food and beverage business, launched the Waldorf Astoria brand, and repositioned Hilton in the luxury space. At Caesars, he led the hospitality division, launching Nobu Hotels, Gordon Ramsay restaurants, and Drai’s Nightlife, contributing 200 million dollars in new revenue. At Starwood, he developed strategic plans for the Board, driving market share gains for category leading lifestyle brands. 

Alexander started his career in management consulting at Deloitte and Strategos, delivering billions in new revenue and lines of business for clients like Royal Dutch Shell and Microsoft. He holds an MBA from Harvard Business School (McArthur Fellow), Masters and Bachelors degrees with distinction from Queen’s University in Canada (Aga Khan Foundation Scholar). He also completed MIT’s executive program in Artificial Intelligence, where he studied machine learning, robotics, natural language processing, and the application of AI in business transformation.

Alexander is the author of Talent Disruption: Leveraging AI to Scale Human Capital (BEP Press, 2023) and a board advisor at Cornell's Institute on Human Capital and Kiwitech Technologies. Named one of the world’s top 100 hospitality executives and among Canada’s top 10 international leaders, he was also honored with the Mayor’s Volunteer Creed from the City of Toronto for his community work with minority youth.

name: Jeff Halevy
title: Technology + Wellness Founder, TV Host
about:
Jeff Halevy is a an entrepreneur and founder with extensive experience in the wellness, technology, and media sectors. 

ENTREPRENEUR & FOUNDER
He has successfully created and navigated various wellness ventures to exits in technology, fitness, AI, and software, both in the online and offline realms. 

Jeff currently serves as the CEO of Continuum, a wellness technology company that deploys its technology in its luxury private wellness clubs, the first of which opened in Fall 2024 in Greenwich Village, NYC. 

PUBLIC HEALTH LEADER
Jeff has dedicated himself to public health advocacy, which is most notable through his appointment by Michelle Obama to create and lead a technology-based program for her "Let's Move!" childhood obesity campaign. 

MEDIA & SPEAKING
Jeff has also made a significant impact through media as a former health correspondent on NBC's "Today Show" and as the host of the globally syndicated TV show "Workout From Within with Jeff Halevy," which currently reaches audiences in over 30 countries. 

Jeff has delivered many keynotes for organizations like AIG, AARP, UBS, Bloomberg, and Entrepreneurs' Organization. 

He has also served as a reporter for various news outlets including US News & World Report and HuffPost. 

PRESS
Jeff's ventures and career have been extensively featured in esteemed outlets including Bloomberg, CNBC, Fortune, Inc. Magazine, and The New York Post.

PERSONAL LIFE
Jeff is a father to two and has successfully competed in powerlifting, jiujitsu, and Muay Thai. He enjoys learning about abstract psychology, philosophy, and psychedelic medicine.

name: Justin McCoy
title: Co-Founder & CEO at Scope
about:
I am a Co-Founder and the CEO of Scope - where we are on a mission to dramatically increase the operational safety of critical rope applications by getting the right data to to the right people in real-time,  before a catastrophic event occurs. The failure of critical rope applications is frequently the result of the inadequate visual inspection that is standard best practice in so many industries - Construction, Maritime Mooring, Mining, Oil & Gas / Drilling, the list goes on. When these ropes fail, people lose their lives and companies lose their reputations. 

At Scope, we address the safety of these critical rope applications with the latest advancements technology has to offer. We are currently focused on Electric Utility Construction and Maintenance where we are equipping operators with the ability to know the break strength of their pulling lines - without actually breaking them. This means no more "educated guesses" on whether or not the line is fit for service. Companies can confidently know that their lines are fit for the task. 

------- 

Committed to leveraging the power of technology and innovative design to tackle formidable issues, I have amassed 15+ years of experience in collaborating with diverse teams across governmental and private sectors to address unique challenges. As a highly motivated leader, I am passionate about employing agile methodologies and design thinking in my work.

I'm Henry, CEO and Co-founder of Senteon. We focus on enhancing cybersecurity posture by streamlining the OS hardening process. My goal is to help organizations safeguard their digital assets and foster a proactive security mindset.

🎯 OUR TARGET MARKET

Senteon caters to businesses of all sizes looking to strengthen their security measures and mitigate potential risks. Our platform offers automation, ease of use, change tracking, and compliance features, all aimed at optimizing your cybersecurity strategy.

🔒 SECURITY RECOMMENDATIONS

Our solution provides security baselines for workstations and servers based on industry best practices such as CIS, NIST, MITRE, and DISA STIG. Automate OS hardening with Senteon, saving valuable time and resources, and enabling your team to focus on other crucial tasks.

🌟 SENTEON'S DIFFERENCE

Senteon's tailored baselines enforce robust OS settings while minimizing end-user disruptions. Our "preventative" security approach offers a strong foundation for defense-in-depth, limiting attack vectors commonly exploited by cybercriminals. Experience a comprehensive, scalable, and user-friendly OS hardening solution with Senteon.

🛡️ THE IMPORTANCE OF OS HARDENING

OS hardening is a critical aspect of a comprehensive cybersecurity strategy. By reducing the attack surface, it becomes more challenging for attackers to exploit vulnerabilities. Senteon's automation streamlines this process, providing a more secure environment for businesses and reducing the risk of data breaches.

📃 COMPLIANCE MADE SIMPLE

Senteon simplifies compliance with regulations such as CMMC v2.0, FFIEC-CAT, HIPAA, PCI DSSv4, and SOC 2. Our platform generates audit-ready reports to showcase your security posture, including real-time change tracking.

🤝 LET'S CONNECT

name: Harpreet Singh
title:
I write about AI,Agents, Entrepreneurship & Meditation | Founder with Exit | 
Head of AI, VP Product@CloudBees | co-CEO/founder@Launchable | Ex-Atlassian/Sun | Author | Angel
about:
I’ve always been captivated by the thrill of building from scratch and a passion for cutting-edge technologies. I came to the US in the late '90s to pursue a Master’s in AI (my thesis was in AI Agents) —only to discover the field was still in its early stages. I found Java instead and fell in love with it.

My journey in Silicon Valley started as an engineer at Sun Microsystems (the home of Java!), crafting enterprise Java EE & GlassFish OSS App Server, but it was at Persistent Systems—a small startup at the time—that I caught the entrepreneurial bug. 

While at Sun, I discovered Jenkins, bet on its transformative potential, and became its first Product Manager and Product Marketing Manager.

This foresight led me to CloudBees, where as VP of Product Management, I helped find product-market fit and scaled the company from $0 to $50M ARR on Enterprise Jenkins. Later, as GM of Atlassian Bitbucket Cloud, I witnessed the power of Atlassian’s famed PLG motion firsthand.

In 2019, fueled by these experiences, I co-founded Launchable Inc., using AI to revolutionize software testing (finally fulfilling my dream of landing in the US to do something with AI :-)). Backed by top-tier VCs like Battery Ventures, Unusual Ventures, and 645 Ventures, we scaled the business until its successful acquisition by CloudBees in 2024. A brief stint as an Entrepreneur-in-Residence (EIR) at Matrix Partners also offered me valuable insights from the investor’s lens.


Career Highlights:

- Co-Head of AI and VP of Product at CloudBees

- Co-founder and CEO of Launchable Inc. (acquired by CloudBees in 2024)

- Scaled CloudBees from $0 to $50M ARR as Head of Product Management

- Head of Product/GM for Atlassian Bitbucket Cloud, experiencing Atlassian's PLG motion

- Engineer/Product Manager/Group Product Marketing Manager in the Java EE division at Sun Microsystems

- Entrepreneur-in-Residence (EIR) at Matrix Partners (brief stint)

Additional Passions:

- Write on AI & Entrepreneurship (aientrepreneurship.substack.com), 

- Write on Meditation formeditators.com, exploring mindfulness and personal growth

- I also advise startups about Product Management, GTM, Marketing, and Engineering

name: Kohsuke Kawaguchi
title: I help software development and product leaders ship 2-5x faster without risk
about:
80% of software tests are pointless. The problem is we just don’t know which 80%. 

Software development and product leaders come to Launchable when they feel that:

➡️  Issues are found too late in the development cycle and releases get delayed.

➡️  Long testing cycles become a bottleneck in the delivery velocity.

➡️  Too much WIP & not enough in production as developers cannot push changes fast enough.

➡️  Unhappy developers, because they are juggling too many WIP balls.

➡️  Testing infrastructure costs are increasing but the testing queue is only getting longer. 

After working together software engineering and product leaders walk away feeling proactive, ahead of the curve because:

1️⃣  Their developers and releases fail fast as issues were found earlier.

2️⃣  Shorter testing loops (reducing hours to minutes) and development cycles (days to hours).

3️⃣  Developers push code to production earlier and have less WIP.

4️⃣  Developers are happier because they get lightning-fast feedback and don’t have to juggle too many balls.

5️⃣  Leaders are spending less on testing infrastructure yet the test queue is shorter.

✅  Most important, development and product leaders get the *CONFIDENCE* they can shorten development cycles and ship new products and features in weeks, not months…without increasing risk or complicating the development workflow.
Running pointless tests slows up development velocity. We’ll help you get ahead of the curve by showing you the 20% of tests that matter. Launchable’s machine learning identifies and runs the tests with the highest probability of failing (based on code/test metadata) to speed up the dev feedback loop and velocity.

WHAT OTHERS SAY:

“My test runtime went down 90%. Deployment to Heroku went from 30 to 10 minutes. It is great, just great!” 
- Masayuki Oguni, CEO, Manba

“Launchable saves us 25% of resources on the mainline build while going faster.” 
- Senior Test Engineer, Car IT GMBH

“Launchable has helped our small team ship code faster and really sped up pushing small changes through” 
- Lead developer, Web Company

“Our goal is to reduce lead to release by one third in 2021 as a result of bringing in Launchable” 
- Senior Engineering Manager, Restaurant POS, Inc

CURIOUS TO LEARN MORE?

📞 Discover why the most innovative development and product teams are using Launchable: launchableinc.com

name: Brian Lent
title: Founder | CEO | CTO | Investor | Board Member | AI-Pioneer in AI, Data, Cloud/Edge Computing
about:
An AI pioneer who has been at the forefront of data science, machine learning, and leading-edge AI technology companies for over three decades.  At Auger, lead development of Analytics and Data platforms to build the leading AI-driven platform for Supply Chains around the world.

As the Co-Founder and CEO of Plunk, introduced a new evolution of analytics via the first generative AI-driven analytics platform for the world’s largest asset class-residential real estate. Plunk was acquired by Home.AI in 2024.

Prior to Plunk, founded one of the largest mobile AI companies, Medio Systems, supporting 440+ million consumers in over 100+ countries. In 2014, Medio was acquired by Nokia (HERE Technologies), and joined as its Chief Technology Officer. As CTO lead a worldwide R&D organization and spearheaded the company’s primary technology roadmap and strategic direction including product innovation, research, and overall AI technology development and strategy. 

Previous to HERE, spent much of my earlier career leading groundbreaking analytics and data-driven systems for companies including IBM and Junglee, acquired by Amazon in 1998. At Amazon, created the company’s first large-scale AI & data analytics platform, formed its analytic infrastructure and integrated Junglee’s recommendations engine into Amazon’s data-driven consumer UX and predictive analytics system – which ultimately today drive 30+% of Amazon sales.  I also lead a fintech spin-off from Amazon, Intelligent Results, applying real-time NLP & predictive text analytics-decades prior to the advent of LLMs--to build an improved FICO score that was acquired by First Data Corp (FDC).

While earning a Masters and Ph.D. candidacy at Stanford University in Computer Science, in 1995 I co-founded with fellow student Sergey Brin "Mining Data at Stanford" (MiDAS), the research lab where we incubated the Google crawler and search engine. Prior to Stanford, founded my first company, Micro Revelations, an early pioneer of AI-driven PC computer games, acquired by Electronic Arts.

A recipient of both the prestigious National Science Foundation and Department of Defense Office of Naval Research Graduate Fellowships, I have the honor of being a key industry thought leader and author of numerous professional publications and patents. In 2008-2009 became a member of the World Economic Forum, selected as a technology visionary pioneer for innovations in mobile-optimized AI. Today I invest-in and have board positions in tech companies and am a member of the Founding Board of the University of Washington Information School.

name: Abtin Buergari
title: Investor & Entrepreneur (3 successful exits)
location: Washington, District of Columbia, United States
about:
I’m a 2x Inc500 founder/entrepreneur that has started, grown, and sold multiple companies. 

I’m curious and don’t accept the status quo if my instincts tell me they could be better. 

I got my meaningful start in entrepreneurship after joining the legal industry, where I built great technology and one of our industry’s fastest growing companies. 

I then shifted my attention to advertising; with a few friends, I co-founded Model B - a now highly awarded digital advertising agency. I was interested in the use of data to understand consumer behavior. 

After 6 years of wrestling with existing technology for measuring, optimizing and drawing insights from massive advertising campaigns, I decided to build something better. 

The biggest problem was complexity. While many pieces of technology sought to answer what you should do with your ad dollars, they require an army of analysts, platform experts, and expensive subscriptions. 

In 2022, I spun out of our agency a technology that aims to shepherd in a new era of advertising that anyone can use and get incredible results. It guides the marketing team and simplifies all the key decision points. 

Blueprint will empower the future of commerce and media management. 

We are now working to bring Blueprint to the advertising industry.

I connect and become friends with other creative founders, CEOs, and executives that are altering how the world currently works. 

Feel free to email me abtin.buergari@blueprint.tech to schedule a 15-minute introduction.

name: Alon Gilady
title: Co-Founder & CEO at Renovai- we're hiring!
about:
As Co-Founder of Renovai, I apply my expertise in retail technology, customer psychology, and visual commerce to drive innovation in virtual interior design. Leveraging cutting-edge technologies such as computer vision, large language models, image analysis, and Generative AI, Renovai delivers a state-of-the-art AI assistant for lifestyle e-commerce retailers. 

Our platform enhances the online shopping experience by enabling customers to visualize furniture in their space, select decor that matches their personal taste and style, and view their options in photorealistic 3D, effectively acting as an AI stylist and designer.

Prior to founding Renovai, I served as CEO of Frame by Frame, where I spearheaded the creation of unique toys, activities, and collectibles in collaboration with premier sports and entertainment brands. I successfully launched the company, secured licensing deals with industry giants such as Nickelodeon, Hasbro, and WWE, and expanded our distribution network to over 20,000 points of sale throughout Europe, including major retailers and independent outlets.

In addition to my entrepreneurial ventures, I have a background in tennis coaching and hold a bachelor’s degree in Economics and Philosophy from Tel Aviv University. This diverse experience informs my approach to business and product development in the tech space.

name: Shawn Ring
title: Founder, President and CEO at Avodah + AvodahMed | Leader in AI | Language | Healthcare | Graduate Professor
about:
In a nutshell, about Shawn. 
Technologist, Applying Artificial Intelligent, Business Leader, Speaker, Connector, Healthcare and Language  advocate

About Avodah
Avodah is an advanced technology company that provides a new AI-enabled platform for language translation and Digital Healthcare services.  Avodah is exceptionally positioned to serve language and digital health care using machine learning, machine translation, computer vision, deep learning, and neural networks. We apply the latest in software to solve customer problems in innovative ways.

Avodah started by translating the #1 selling book in the world into new languages of all models, including American Sign Language, and offering translation, transcription, language preservation, and language re-education tools.

AvodahMed, using the same AI technology as Avodah, provides an AI-enabled Digital Healthcare Platform.  The platform has improved audio/video communication with enhanced visual recognition, collection of vitals, language transcription and translation, clinical and clinical environmental insights, and EMR integration. We facilitate an experience aimed to exceed a live visit!

Avodah cares how we make technology.  We ensure the technology connects an English speaker to an ASL signer by enabling language translation.  The same technology connects a doctor to a patient with advanced communication and visual recognition.  Our human-centered Ai technology allows a patient-centered platform where language or location will not limit.  Avodah makes you limitless. 

Avodah’s culture focuses on delivering our services with innovation, generosity, excellence, and speed.  These four values give a unique perspective – our values guide our culture inside and outside the company. 


About Me
I have grown several technology-based start-ups to strategic success and developed multi-national operations and legal foundations in Singapore, South Africa, Fiji, and the United States. I’ve led Mergers and Acquisitions of more than nine technology companies. 29 years of experience in International and Domestic businesses with start-up growth exceeding $130m in annual reoccurring revenues in SAAS B2C and B2B models. I have a passion for seeing people impacted for good, and we pride ourselves on a healthy work-life balance. Avodah’s culture and employee satisfaction are paramount.

name: Bill Portelli
title: Board Director, Operating Chairman, CEO Advisor
about:
Bill is Board Member and operating executive credited for his exceptional track record in driving exponential growth and creating substantial enterprise value across diverse industry sectors. He has led technology companies as a CEO, Advisor, and Board Director to deliver billions of dollars in revenue and market capitalization.

Currently serving as the Head of Strategy at a pioneering AI company, Bill spearheads initiatives that push the boundaries of AI. Simultaneously, he holds Board seats at early to mid-stage venture-backed technology firms, where his strategic acumen fuels their expansion efforts.

Drawing upon his expertise in SaaS, chip design, product and GTM strategies, Bill has founded, restructured and led early stage to Fortune 500 companies. As an SVP/GM and Corporate Officer at public companies like Cadence and CTT he drove innovation in the semiconductor and EDA markets. As founding CEO of CollabNet, he built the first company to commercialize software development in the cloud.

Bill's contributions to technology innovation have earned him global recognition, including the Davos Technology Pioneer Award from the World Economic Forum for contributions in cloud computing, DevOps, and open source.

BOARD & CEO ADVISOR ROLES
•	Board Member/Advisor roles to CEOs on team growth and alignment, product innovation, revenue acceleration using a range of GTM models, M&A, and fundraising
•	Trusted by employees, partners, customers, board members and investors. Leads by example. 
•	Founded and scaled an enterprise SaaS company leveraging open source and cloud to $70M in revenue and an exit
•	Led mid-stage company to a 500% revenue increase in 3 years to an IPO and a $440M acquisition

FORTUNE 1000 LEADERSHIP
•	Realigned both private and public companies into BU structures to drive market position, agility, product innovation and revenue growth
•	Led $500M product and service BUs within a $1B+ company to profitable high-growth
•	Acquired companies, built channels, and established partnerships with SIs and resellers

PRODUCT & STRATEGY
•	Transforms company strategies and segments, product/market fit, sales engines, and operating plans with a focus on winning teams and customer satisfaction
•	Established a multi-million OS Subversion community and the industry’s first DevOps SaaS cloud
•	Recognized as a World Economic Forum Davos Technology Pioneer for leadership in SaaS, open source, and DevOps
•	Noted author on both enterprise growth and Product-Led Growth strategies

about:
👋 I’m Eric Chebil, Managing Broker and Founder of Cher® and Nest Navigate — on a mission to redefine the path to homeownership through education, technology, and innovation.

After starting my career at Swinerton Builders and earning my LEED® AP credential, I transitioned from commercial construction to founding Cher®, a real estate edtech company featured in Forbes for our unique approach to housing. Cher® empowers Realtors and Loan Officers through tools, coaching, and co-ownership options—built to meet today’s affordability challenges head-on.

Most recently, I launched Nest Navigate, a completely separate company focused on gamified homebuyer education. Nest Navigate is designed for first-time renters and buyers who want to learn at their own pace—and get rewarded while doing it. Through personalized AI-driven courses and a Nest Coin rewards system, we’re making financial literacy fun, accessible, and motivating.

I believe the future of real estate lies in transparency, education, and accessibility—and I’m proud to lead ventures that are working to build that future.

about:
Champion of World Class Automation and Fulfillment
20+ Years of System Design, Software Implementation and Supply Chain Excellence
Director Level Solution Design Engineer, People Manager and Team Builder.

I love the supply chain industry.  It is the heart of our world economy.  My efforts make U.S. companies more efficient in the world market allowing more companies to grow, stay in the U.S. and serve my fellow citizens.  That is my superpower.

As with most individuals that advance through companies, I have become more of a team building and people manager than an engineer.  My philosophy as a team builder is best articulated by the authors of the following books: ‘The 5 Dysfunctions of a Team’ by P. Lencioni, ‘The Speed of Trust’ by Stephen M.R. Covey and ‘Leaders Eat Last’ by Simon Sinek. It is of upmost importance to me to work with, and develop, high quality teams that produce outstanding individuals.
 
My operational and consulting philosophies are best described through the books ‘The Goal’ by Eliyahu Goldratt and ‘Getting Naked’ by Patrick Lencioni. When it comes to system design or operation, I view the process to be of utmost importance - over and beyond whichever technology is used. While I am a Champion of World Class Automation and Fulfillment, I believe you get there through process, continuous improvement, and quality management – not by buying equipment and hoping it does the job for you. And I feel that the above-mentioned books describe very well how to work the problem and build the relationships needed to achieve the initial designs and continuous improvement.
 
And finally … I really enjoy what I do. I truly think that we in logistics design have the most diverse, stimulating, and downright fun profession out there.  

If you would like to learn more, please send me a personalized connection request, inMail, or check out some of the content below.

name: Ramesh Panuganty
title: Anticipated tech trends, crafted solutions, and launched businesses ahead of broad adoption. @HumanTechOS
about:
As creative technology pioneer, with 17 patents and several publications, I anticipated how new technology could be used to innovatively address business, consumer, and industry problems before their rivals did and who helped build new product lines that preempted markets. As an entrepreneur, haunched & exited four start-ups, I envisioned new market solutions as breakthroughs in a highly competitive technology space in different verticals.

At MachEye (acquired by VRNT, Verint), I created a modern analytics platform that gave an actionable "play" button to data. Created custom language models that offer Google-like search and YouTube-like audio-visual experiences, decision-makers at any level can receive actionable insights and recommendations. Unlike traditional analytical platforms that only provide answers to "what" questions on data, MachEye offers a comprehensive solution that enables users to answer "what, why, and how" scenarios for everyone in the organization. 

At SelectQ (acquired by Thinkster in 2020), I created an ed-tech platform that helps students with GetAI test questions on the fly, based on their skill level, providing with the right micro-tuned, generative (not just adaptive) content at the right time for them to master each subject. Using AI and NLG, the platform generates questions stream for all SAT topics , with ratcheting complexity until full preparation. All SelectQ’s profits are committed to the cause of helping needy with in-person STEM topics.

At Drastin (acquired by Splunk in 2017), I created the "Conversational Analytics" as a new BI market category for enterprise adoption, and the product was recognized as the top five AI platforms by Gartner, getting ranked as a "cool vendor" in search-driven data analytics, within just 30 months.

At Cloud360 Hyperplatform (acquired by Cognizant in 2012), I created “Cloud Management Platforms” as a new market category and built a multi-million dollar ARR business with triple-digit yearly revenue uptick. The product was ranked as a leader in MQ, by both Gartner and by 451 Research.

My focus has always been to develop market-leading innovations and breakthroughs, to make a case for them, organize and lead inspired teams, and preempt competition to conquer markets. This mantle required me to not just focus on technology and products, but also on the markets, competition, business growth, team leadership, and optimum resource management.

I share my random thoughts at https://x.com/HumanTechOS

name: Andrew Krause
title: 3x Founder and CEO | Video Marketing & Corporate Communications for Audience Engagement, Earned PR, Paid Media and Experiential Marketing
about:
As a 3x Founder and CEO of AKA MEDIA INC, I’ve learned most business challenges point to some type of communication issue. I work with Fortune 500 executives, business owners and nonprofits to solve those business challenges.

I created AKA MEDIA PARTNERS LLC in 2019 as a video-first marketing and communications company to specifically solve business challenges using video content for employee and customer engagement, earned PR, paid media and experiential marketing.

Our award-winning teams offer a unique alternative to advertising, digital and social agencies. We draw on our extensive backgrounds to spearhead strategic marketing communications campaigns collaborating with real people, celebrities, athletes and CEOs. We know how to take advantage of moments that matter. We know whose attention to capture and how to generate genuine reactions. We know the right nuance to explore and we consistently deliver unforgettable brand impact.

Before I founded AKA in 1998, I began my career working for Fleishman, Edelman and Golin where l learned from the best in the fields of marketing, communications, brand management and public relations. I quickly became a trusted, go-to partner and resource for top accounts including McDonald's, Campbell Soup and MillerCoors. As a budding entrepreneur in college, I led a 40-person staff for Pyramid Public Relations, a PRSSA Student-Run Agency while working part-time with Jimmy John to open the 2nd Jimmy John’s location.

Over my 30-year career, I’ve been fortunate to connect with the most influential people in the world working with brands as the lead for celebrity activations and sponsorships. As a Goldman Sachs 10K Small Businesses graduate, I’ve learned from business leaders including Warren Buffet, Michael Bloomberg, Sara Blakely, Jo Malone and Richard Branson. I enjoy working with entrepreneurs in several industry and entrepreneurial groups while volunteering with the Three Pillars Initiative, an organization teaching high school juniors and seniors the art and science of philanthropy.

In 2024, I founded KRAUSE BROS. LLC as a holding company aligned with my pasion projects and philanthropic activity. I’m available for advisory positions and will recruit, build and elevate teams of experts to deliver results. I’m the 2025 President-Elect for PRSA Chicago, the nation’s third largest chapter.

I graduated Southern Illinois University with a BS in speech communications and minors in journalism, public relations and marketing and continue to support the university and its Alumni Association.

name: Raj Koneru
title: Founder | Supporting ambitious CXOs growth with AI and Data | Multiple Patents |Follow for posts about improving your business with AI and Data
about:
Twenty-five years in data taught me one hard truth: When data fails or slows down, so does everything else — decisions, teams, growth. 

Over the years, I’ve watched too many C-suite executives make the wrong decision— or no 
decision at all—because their data team needed “just one more week,” and they were left 
with their gut instincts or pulling numbers in Excel. I’ve seen businesses miss targets and leave serious money on the table — not because they didn't have data, but because it lacked the context and clarity to take the right next step. And I’ve seen promising AI initiatives lose their way — stuck waiting on pipelines that simply couldn’t keep up. 

The root cause was always the same: traditional data engineering simply wasn’t built for the speed, complexity, and pace of change in modern business. 

Every data request becomes a project—weeks of design, development, and validation. And when the question changes? You start over from scratch. 

So, I spent the last few years building what I wished had existed all along — a way to deliver integrated, accurate, actionable data instantly, without the delays, backlogs, or budget drains of traditional engineering cycles. 

That's Anvizent. 

Anvizent is a generative data pipeline platform powered by an agentic data management engine. Anvizent delivers integrated, accurate, actionable data - at the speed and scale of decision-making and AI.   

No data engineering cycles. No delays. 

You just follow 3 simple steps: 

Step 1: Define Your Data Requirements - Your business teams and analysts — not IT — configure the data requirements and business rules.
Step 2: Generate - Instantly generate complete pipelines that deliver integrated, accurate, actionable data. 
Step 3: Regenerate - When business rules or requirements change, simply regenerate pipelines instantly. 

What used to take weeks of data engineering now happens near-instantly. 

The results are transformative: 

- Near Instant access to integrated, accurate, actionable data delivered into your workflow 
- 90% reduction in resource requirements — one business analyst can now do the work of an entire data engineering team.  
 - 30% lower storage and data processing costs

name: Haitham Al-Beik
title: Devoted to a Human-Centric future & #breezeLife movement
about:
Haitham Al-Beik is a visionary entrepreneur, innovator, and thought leader renowned for his human-centric approach to technology and business. As the CEO and founder of Wings, a pioneering research and development lab, he focuses on creating autonomous, sustainable businesses through advanced robotics and AI. Wings aims to revolutionize the services industry—including food and beverage, hospitality, and other in-person services—by introducing next-generation infrastructure and robotic systems that are more efficient, environmentally friendly, and accessible to entrepreneurs without traditional business experience.

Haitham advocates for the transition from smart cities to intuitive cities, emphasizing the need to innovate within the services industry to align with his concept of the "Sustainable Human." He believes the industry needs its own "lab" to revolutionize it—similar to how Bell Labs and Silicon Valley transformed other sectors—fostering a new era of human-centric innovation. He is also pioneering "The Human-Centric Approach: A Manifesto" (coming soon), which emphasizes the integration of technology with human well-being.

In his role as the Director of Human-Centric Innovations and Evangelist at Expo City Dubai, Haitham spearheads the city's strategy to foster creativity and contribute to a harmonious urban landscape. With nearly two decades of experience in urban development, sustainable and autonomous business models, and multiple startups across the UAE and the US, he blends technology and sustainability to unlock human potential.

Haitham is a distinguished speaker, thought leader, and futurist with expertise spanning entrepreneurship, sustainability, education, mental well-being, and the evolution of future cities. He has a keen interest in automation technology, robotics, and AI. Among his innovative projects is HiveRobotics, a suite of purpose-built robots capable of autonomously performing various tasks, enhancing efficiency and reducing labor needs in dynamic environments like retail and restaurants.

Beyond his technological endeavors, Haitham is an advocate for sustainable urban living. He promotes the #breezeLife Movement, encouraging a shift towards conscious living and the redesign of urban spaces to prioritize well-being, creativity, and empowerment. His vision emphasizes creating environments where people can thrive by leveraging automation and AI to handle mundane tasks, freeing individuals to focus on their passions and personal growth.

For more information about Haitham's work and philosophy, please visit albeik.com.

name: Tim Shih
title: Wolfberry | YPO 305 & Pacific Rim
about:
As Founding Principal of Wolfberry, Tim invests his time, resources and capital in people, companies and causes that he believes in. After obtaining a shiny Computer Science degree from Yale University, Tim began his journey as a software engineer working on wireless mesh sensor networks, a precursor to IoT technology. For reasons he still needs to explain to this day, Tim "pivoted" into law, obtaining a J.D. from Duke University and practicing at the New York office of Cravath, Swaine & Moore LLP, where he specialized in securities, M&A and corporate law. Tim then took his skills across the Pacific to Beijing, China where he tried his hand in entertainment law bringing Hollywood films into China including: Iron Man 3, Looper, Twilight and Transcendence. It was in Beijing, and then Shanghai, that Tim began his entrepreneurial journey, founding a private equity fund focused on financing large scale real estate projects in the United States and specifically, Florida, utilizing international capital. Over time, this grew from purely real estate financing to real estate sales, investment and development with a presence around the world including:  Miami, Fort Lauderdale, New York, San Diego, Silicon Valley, Beijing, Shanghai, Shenzhen, and Istanbul. 
 
Tim continues to keep his legal mind sharp as a founding partner of Yee & Shih, LLP and his real estate mind focused as a founding partner of OneWorld Group. In addition, Tim is a member of YPO Pacific Rim where he serves as an executive officer as well as on the North Asia regional board. The son of Taiwanese immigrants, Tim gives back to the community as the President of the Taiwanese Junior Chamber of Commerce in San Diego. Tim is an active angel investor and is a member of Tech Coast Angels - San Diego and Miami Angels.
notable_achievements: Distinguished Engineering Alumni Award from Santa Clara University (2014); Over 480 publications in computer science and engineering; Founder of the International Journal of Distance Education Technologies; Recipient of multiple international research awards including National Science Council of Taiwan, IIAS Germany, HSSS Greece, Brandon Hall USA, and Google MOOC Focused Research Award

I'm a lifelong entrepreneur with a strong drive for personal growth, a desire for both myself and those around me. If we're not growing, we're dying.

name: Michael Turner
title: Founder & CEO of Verify4 | President of PERC | Serial Social Entrepreneur
about:
A serial social entrepreneur, Dr. Turner is co-founder and CEO of Verify4--a disruptive mutli-state network solution for real-time income and employment verification. Verify4 wins massively in coverage (above 90% per state), user experience (esign) and price (sorry monopolist). While still in soft launch, Verify4 will rapidly achieve scale and forever change the verifications space. 

Verify4 and Dr. Turner's other sojourns into the private sector were inspired by his commitment to end "credit invisibility" (a term he coined) through the use of alternative data. Dr. Turner also collaborated with Experian MicroAnalytics on a prospective alternative credit bureau in East Africa (Financial Identity Risk Management or FIRM), an alterantive data credit score for smallholder farmers in India in partnership with eKutir (Finance and Agriculture Risk Management or FARM); and a cutting edge verifications firm in partnership with FIS Certegy (VIE-ability) 

Dr. Turner currently serves as President and CEO and Founder of the Policy and Economic Research Council (PERC). PERC is a non-profit policy research center focusing upon economic development that has advised governments on five continents. They are global thought leaders on issues of access to finance and credit information sharing.

PERC is committed to outcomes rather than sound bites. PERC only develops solutions to asset building challenges that are sustainable in the market. Using information solutions, PERC seeks to increase financial inclusion by more than any single institution on earth

After serving as a Graduate Fellow at the Columbia Institute for Tele-Information (CITI) at the Columbia Business School in New York City, he was named Executive Director of the Information Services Executive Council (ISEC).

Dr. Turner has testified before Congress and numerous state legislatures, and presented studies to a host of domestic and foreign government agencies including the White House (CEA and NEC) on credit issues. He served on the Brookings Institution’s Urban Markets Initiative Advisory Board, served as an advisor to the Obama campaign on urban policy, and completed a two-year term on the US DHS Data Privacy Advisory Committee. He has also served as an expert witness before federal court on FCRA matters.

Turner received his Ph.D. from Columbia University in Political Economy, and a B.A. in economics from Miami University. Turner is an affiliate scholar at the Alfred P. Sloan Foundation and a Fellow at the Ashoka Foundation.

Danny Davis is a visionary investor and entrepreneur with an impressive track record spanning over two decades in the technology industry. name: Steve Latham
title: Founder & CEO @ Canopy |  Leadership Development
about:
👋 Howdy! Claire here, Founder & CEO at Canopy. Thanks so much for stopping by. 

My life’s mission is to help people become happier at work. This has shaped everything I do. Over the past decade, I’ve helped 50,000+ managers at companies like Amazon, Netflix, and Shopify through live sessions, tailored programs, and practical leadership tools.

My journey started over ten years ago, when my first client was 37signals, the creators of Basecamp. I went on to spin off a product they’d developed internally into a tool that became part of Canopy’s broader platform. Since then, I’ve distilled over 50 years of leadership research into frameworks that help leaders navigate complexity and lead with clarity, confidence, and care.

Along the way, I’ve coached leaders at Apple, Uber, and other leading companies through tough moments — team dynamics, performance challenges, scaling pains — and helped them find a way forward. I’ve also spoken at conferences and led leadership trainings around the world. My insights have been featured in Harvard Business Review, CNBC, Inc., and Fortune, and I’ve taught entrepreneurship at Northwestern University, my alma mater.

At Canopy, we help fast-moving organizations upskill their managers through:

🌱 Leadership Development Programs: Live, cohort-based training tailored to your org’s real-world challenges.

💬 Coaching & Advising: 1-1 support for leaders navigating high-stakes, high-complexity moments.

🎤 Speaking & Workshops: Keynotes and interactive sessions that spark clarity and shift culture.

📱 The Canopy App: A leadership improvement app that delivers personalized daily insights, just-in-time tools, and an AI Assistant for deeper support when complex challenges arise.

Outside of work, I paint in oils from my studio in Point Reyes, California, and live in the Bay Area with my husband.

If you’re thinking about how to better support your leaders — or just want to chat about what it means to lead well in fast-moving environments — I’d love to connect.

📩 claire@canopy.is  |   💌 newsletter.canopy.is (link in my profile)

Our software solutions are not designed to merely increase the productivity of human labour in a linear and direct way. Instead, our software seeks to boost the capacity of the human brain by augmenting it through data supremacy and decision precision to power smarter, more informed operations. It is our personal commitment to build significant software solutions that support the survival of vital institutions and the people in it. Because, we will only succeed if and when those institutions operate as intended”  

- Dan Saldi

name: Clement Connor

about:
Clement Connor is the CEO & Founder of Fast Lane Drive, an exclusive exotic car club with locations in Los Angeles, San Diego, Scottsdale, and Las Vegas. Additionally, he is the COO and Co-Founder of SMARTBOOST, a San Diego-based marketing agency specializing in AI-powered marketing strategies. Founded in late 2014, Clement has played an instrumental role in growing SMARTBOOST from a two-person venture in a coffee shop to a thriving company with over 20 employees and nearly 100 clients.

A native of Paris, Clement moved to the United States in 2008, driven by his entrepreneurial spirit and the desire to pursue the American dream. He is dedicated to helping businesses expand their marketing and sales initiatives. Alongside his entrepreneurial pursuits, Clement is an avid philanthropist, contributing to charities such as Voices for Children, Namaste Wings to Fly, Make-A-Wish Foundation, Leukemia Society, and the San Diego Police Foundation.

In addition to his professional accomplishments, Clement has a keen interest in social activities, and enjoys spending his leisure time skiing, wakeboarding, water skiing, and car racing.

My goal is to change health incentives. Right now, every lever of our system profits when Americans are more sick. They should be incentivized to promote disease reversal and prevention.

name: David Greenberg
title: President & CEO, Simply Speaking, Inc. -- Award-Winning Executive Communication Skills Coaching
about:
The first time I spoke to a group was back in junior high school—Mrs. Weir’s Sixth-grade English class. Oral book reports. I approached the front of the room, clenched the lectern for support and managed to squeak out five words: "Good afternoon, my name is." I completely froze, forgot my name, and never even started the book report! 

Years later I discovered that if one learns how to prepare, practice, and truly connect with listeners, public speaking could be a wonderfully rewarding experience. I studied the best communicators and, though still nervous, I sought every opportunity to speak. Eventually I won several speaking competitions. 

In 1988, Toastmasters International honored me with the title “State's Best Speech Coach” and my company, Simply Speaking, Inc.®, was born. Oglethorpe University in Atlanta hired me to teach their executive presentation skills classes and people from all types of organizations called me to help them improve their communication skills. A decade later, the National Speakers Association honored me with their highest-earned award, the Certified Speaking Professional. The "CSP" designation is held by less than 7% of the organization’s 4000 professional speakers.
 
Over the last 30+ years, I've assembled a team of stellar coaches. Together we have helped more than 100,000 people from Savannah to Singapore to develop extraordinary communication skills.

My goal is not to impress you but to impress upon you that no matter where you or your team may be on the spectrum of communication skills, with the right tools, the right coaching methods, and the right support, virtually anyone can be a highly effective and respected communicator.
speaking_engagements: The No-Sweat Way to Prepare and Deliver Winning Presentations™; Thriving in the Midst of Change!: A unique on your feet team building experience; How to Work with and Sell to Different Personality Styles: Understanding personality styles; Forget Your Title, We’re All in Sales™; 60 Simple Ways to Keep Your Audience Riveted; The big lesson: Don’t dilute your message!; Three magical phrases to get people listening; How to connect with your audience; How to reduce presentation anxiety

about:
Manuel brings 20 years of hands-on Silicon Valley experience to MaiVERIC. He is a strategic thinker at heart, with a broad understanding of emerging technologies, capable of identifying and assessing trends, assembling and coordinating cross-functional teams, structuring deals, negotiating terms, and bringing new products and services to market.

While at Intel, he was also responsible for developing and bringing to market consumer apps in the enhanced photography space, leveraging Intel’s computer vision (RealSense) technology.
 
As a Managing Director at Monroy Petersen, Manuel also serves as an advisor to businesses in the U.S. and Mexico in the areas of strategic planning and mergers & acquisitions. He is currently very active advising multinational corporations searching for operational (nearshoring) efficiencies from the relocation of manufacturing plants into Mexico.

Prior to Monroy Petersen, Manuel was part of Andersen's Global Corporate Finance practice, where he managed buy-side and sell-side transactions of high-growth venture-backed companies and worked in deals with Cisco, Microsoft, IBM and Amazon. While at Andersen, he was responsible for identifying emerging growth sectors and for generating the group's proprietary research used by the U.S. and European corporate finance teams. At Andersen he obtained his General Securities Representative license from the NASD (Series 7 & 63).
 
Manuel started his career with the Latin America M&A group of New York based Bankers Trust, now part of Deutsche Bank, and also worked for California Commerce Bank, a subsidiary of Citigroup. He holds a Master's degree in Finance and Business Strategy from the Anderson School at UCLA, and a Bachelor of Science degree in Industrial and Systems Engineering from USC.  He is also an IBA Accredited Business Appraiser.

name: Ioannis Tsamardinos
title: CEO & Co-Founder at JADBio
about:
Ioannis Tsamardinos main research concerns three directions (a) the development of novel, state-of-the-art algorithms and theory for Machine Learning, Bayesian Network learning, Variable Selection, and Causal Discovery; the methods are inspired by data analysis problems in biomedicine, (b) application of state-of-the-art data analysis methods in biomedical data to discover new domain knowledge, and (c) the development of automated systems for facilitating data analysis for non-expert users. Prof. Tsamardinos has over 110 publications in international journals, conferences, and books. He has also participated in several applied projects (including US and EU funded projects) to biomedicine, including the analysis of clinical, epidemiological, microarray gene-expression, flow cytometry, mass cytometry, proteomics and text-categorization. Distinctions with colleagues and students include the best performance in one of the four tasks in the recent First Causality Challenge Competition, ISMB 2005 Best Poster Winner, a Gold Medal in the Student Paper Competition in MEDINFO 2004, the Outstanding Student Paper Award in AIPS 2000, the NASA Group Achievement Award for participation in the Remote Agent team and others. International recognition has led to membership to the Editorial Board Member of the Journal of Artificial Intelligence Research, being an Area Chair for ECML 2011, Senior PC member for IJCAI 2011, and a regular reviewer for some of the leading Machine Learning journals (e.g., JMLR, TKDE, PAMI), bioinformatics journals (e.g., Bioinformatics Journal, BMC Bioinformatics) and machine learning, artificial intelligence and biomedical informatics conferences (e.g., ECML, UAI). Statistics on recognition of work include more than 7000 citations, and h-index of 32 (as estimated by the Publish or Perish tool).

Specialties: machine learning, bioinformatics, intelligent data analysis, data mining, causal discovery, bayesian networks

Thierry is the founder & CEO of Stream (https://getstream.io/). Stream powers activity feeds and chat technology for over a billion end-users.
